WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:16.980 align:middle line:90%


00:00:16.980 --> 00:00:20.040 align:middle line:10%
Hi, I'm Lisa Garr, host of
"Gaiam Inspirations," coming

00:00:20.040 --> 00:00:21.430 align:middle line:10%
to you from our
beautiful studios

00:00:21.430 --> 00:00:23.750 align:middle line:10%
here in Los Angeles, California.

00:00:23.750 --> 00:00:27.060 align:middle line:10%
Did you know that 55
million people a day

00:00:27.060 --> 00:00:30.680 align:middle line:10%
deal with the loss of a
loved one and, on average,

00:00:30.680 --> 00:00:35.290 align:middle line:10%
people can suffer over six
to eight years over grief?

00:00:35.290 --> 00:00:38.100 align:middle line:84%
Would it help you if you knew
that although grieving is

00:00:38.100 --> 00:00:40.900 align:middle line:84%
inevitable, there's a
handbook, so to speak,

00:00:40.900 --> 00:00:44.330 align:middle line:84%
for dealing with
grief in 30 minutes?

00:00:44.330 --> 00:00:47.620 align:middle line:84%
So when that debilitating
grief surfaces,

00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:49.880 align:middle line:84%
there is actually a
step-by-step process

00:00:49.880 --> 00:00:52.140 align:middle line:84%
that can help you
handle the next moment

00:00:52.140 --> 00:00:54.620 align:middle line:90%
with a little bit more peace.

00:00:54.620 --> 00:00:56.550 align:middle line:84%
Even if you're grieving
the loss of a job

00:00:56.550 --> 00:00:59.400 align:middle line:84%
or a divorce or
any other loss, it

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:02.610 align:middle line:84%
helps if you have a grief
coach-- or better yet, you

00:01:02.610 --> 00:01:04.700 align:middle line:90%
become your own grief coach.

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:08.340 align:middle line:84%
And joining me is Aurora Winter,
whose firsthand experience

00:01:08.340 --> 00:01:11.760 align:middle line:84%
with grief taught her how
to help others find a sense

00:01:11.760 --> 00:01:13.220 align:middle line:90%
of peace within the loss.

00:01:13.220 --> 00:01:15.010 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for being here.

00:01:15.010 --> 00:01:16.150 align:middle line:84%
Great to be here
with you, Lisa.

00:01:16.150 --> 00:01:18.150 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: You're so brave,
and you're such an inspiration

00:01:18.150 --> 00:01:19.320 align:middle line:90%
to so many people.

00:01:19.320 --> 00:01:20.230 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:01:20.230 --> 00:01:21.900 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: So tell me
about your experience

00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:25.700 align:middle line:84%
when you suddenly had to handle
an enormous amount of grief.

00:01:25.700 --> 00:01:27.846 align:middle line:10%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah, well,
my story is that, you know,

00:01:27.846 --> 00:01:28.980 align:middle line:10%
I thought my life was perfect.

00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:32.150 align:middle line:10%
And it was just on the cusp
of getting even better.

00:01:32.150 --> 00:01:34.000 align:middle line:10%
My husband and I had
launched a multimillion

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:35.010 align:middle line:10%
dollar business from scratch.

00:01:35.010 --> 00:01:35.876 align:middle line:10%
LISA GARR: Oh my goodness.

00:01:35.876 --> 00:01:37.510 align:middle line:10%
We had a beautiful
four-year-old son,

00:01:37.510 --> 00:01:39.950 align:middle line:10%
who was adorable as only
four-year-olds can be.

00:01:39.950 --> 00:01:42.140 align:middle line:84%
We were building our
dream home on the lake.

00:01:42.140 --> 00:01:44.020 align:middle line:84%
I'd just met Mel
Gibson and Goldie Hawn

00:01:44.020 --> 00:01:45.650 align:middle line:84%
and John Badham, who
directed "Stakeout."

00:01:45.650 --> 00:01:47.050 align:middle line:90%
And so I'm, like, yeah.

00:01:47.050 --> 00:01:48.710 align:middle line:90%
I'm being paved and hired to--

00:01:48.710 --> 00:01:49.570 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Oh my gosh.

00:01:49.570 --> 00:01:50.510 align:middle line:90%
---to write a screenplay.

00:01:50.510 --> 00:01:52.640 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, yeah,
everything's perfect

00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:54.560 align:middle line:90%
and just about to get better.

00:01:54.560 --> 00:01:57.110 align:middle line:84%
And then my 33-year-old
husband died suddenly.

00:01:57.110 --> 00:01:59.221 align:middle line:84%
And he died, you
know, right beside me.

00:01:59.221 --> 00:02:00.610 align:middle line:84%
And--
LISA GARR: Oh.

00:02:00.610 --> 00:02:02.180 align:middle line:90%
It was devastating.

00:02:02.180 --> 00:02:04.900 align:middle line:84%
I felt like my entire
life shattered.

00:02:04.900 --> 00:02:08.120 align:middle line:84%
I felt like Humpty Dumpty,
you know, smashed to pieces.

00:02:08.120 --> 00:02:11.480 align:middle line:84%
And I had no idea how to put
the pieces back together again.

00:02:11.480 --> 00:02:13.300 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: When you
were on such a high

00:02:13.300 --> 00:02:15.220 align:middle line:84%
and then this-- out
of the blue-- I mean,

00:02:15.220 --> 00:02:16.850 align:middle line:84%
sometimes when you're
on that kind of a role,

00:02:16.850 --> 00:02:19.880 align:middle line:84%
you think, oh, nothing bad is
going to happen to me, right?

00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:20.680 align:middle line:90%
I'm super-person, right?

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:23.920 align:middle line:84%
That's how I felt. I felt
like I was in a golden glow.

00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:26.150 align:middle line:84%
And I tried everything
to get better, you know.

00:02:26.150 --> 00:02:28.410 align:middle line:84%
I worked out as if I was
training for the Olympics.

00:02:28.410 --> 00:02:30.900 align:middle line:84%
I read every self-help book
I could get my hands on.

00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:31.930 align:middle line:90%
You know, I did therapy.

00:02:31.930 --> 00:02:34.260 align:middle line:84%
I went to church, but
nothing really helped

00:02:34.260 --> 00:02:36.140 align:middle line:90%
until I put together a recipe.

00:02:36.140 --> 00:02:38.870 align:middle line:84%
First, I stumbled
across it for myself--

00:02:38.870 --> 00:02:40.990 align:middle line:90%
put it into use in my own life.

00:02:40.990 --> 00:02:42.761 align:middle line:84%
And now, that just
changed everything.

00:02:42.761 --> 00:02:44.820 align:middle line:84%
I'm happy.
I'm peaceful and effective.

00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:46.890 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Well, I mean, let
me take you back to that moment

00:02:46.890 --> 00:02:47.956 align:middle line:90%
when you were dealing with that.

00:02:47.956 --> 00:02:49.400 align:middle line:84%
Because you had--
I mean, were you

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:52.540 align:middle line:84%
dealing more with your own
grief or the grief of your son

00:02:52.540 --> 00:02:55.100 align:middle line:84%
that he was-- that your son
was going through or both?

00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:57.250 align:middle line:84%
I mean, did you have
time to grieve yourself?

00:02:57.250 --> 00:02:59.580 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's almost
like asking, like,

00:02:59.580 --> 00:03:02.040 align:middle line:84%
did you have time to
deal with the tidal wave?

00:03:02.040 --> 00:03:05.710 align:middle line:84%
No, you don't have-- you
know, but you have no choice.

00:03:05.710 --> 00:03:07.870 align:middle line:90%
I-- it was so intense for me.

00:03:07.870 --> 00:03:10.070 align:middle line:90%
It was so unexpected.

00:03:10.070 --> 00:03:12.910 align:middle line:84%
And I was so in love
with my husband.

00:03:12.910 --> 00:03:17.530 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I was just hit
with a tidal wave of emotions.

00:03:17.530 --> 00:03:18.620 align:middle line:90%
And it was so raw.

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:21.620 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I was
raped emotionally.

00:03:21.620 --> 00:03:24.780 align:middle line:84%
It was horrific
and heartwrenching.

00:03:24.780 --> 00:03:26.980 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I wanted
to be there for my son.

00:03:26.980 --> 00:03:28.880 align:middle line:84%
But I was not at my best--
LISA GARR: Right.

00:03:28.880 --> 00:03:30.191 align:middle line:90%
---to say the least, yeah.

00:03:30.191 --> 00:03:31.890 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And the questions
that he was asking-- I

00:03:31.890 --> 00:03:34.750 align:middle line:84%
mean, when I read your book,
"From Heartbreak to Happiness,"

00:03:34.750 --> 00:03:36.530 align:middle line:90%
I read it in one night.

00:03:36.530 --> 00:03:40.790 align:middle line:84%
And I was in tears the entire
time because of-- oh, you

00:03:40.790 --> 00:03:43.560 align:middle line:84%
write-- first of all
the journaling process

00:03:43.560 --> 00:03:46.610 align:middle line:84%
that you did that helped you
get through these moments--

00:03:46.610 --> 00:03:48.050 align:middle line:90%
these step-by-step moments.

00:03:48.050 --> 00:03:50.170 align:middle line:84%
How did you get yourself
to be able to even write?

00:03:50.170 --> 00:03:51.751 align:middle line:84%
Some days, it was
just one sentence.

00:03:51.751 --> 00:03:53.149 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:03:53.149 --> 00:03:55.440 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Well, I've written
a diary since I was nine,

00:03:55.440 --> 00:03:57.760 align:middle line:84%
so it wasn't a new
thing that I took on.

00:03:57.760 --> 00:03:59.190 align:middle line:90%
It was a habit.

00:03:59.190 --> 00:04:00.610 align:middle line:84%
And thank God, I had
that because that

00:04:00.610 --> 00:04:01.810 align:middle line:90%
was really my lifeline.

00:04:01.810 --> 00:04:04.990 align:middle line:84%
Because if-- if you can't
feel it, you can't heal it,

00:04:04.990 --> 00:04:05.930 align:middle line:90%
I've since learned.

00:04:05.930 --> 00:04:06.630 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Wow.

00:04:06.630 --> 00:04:08.170 align:middle line:84%
And journaling actually
is a simple thing

00:04:08.170 --> 00:04:10.610 align:middle line:84%
people can do that
will really help them

00:04:10.610 --> 00:04:14.290 align:middle line:84%
discover their own
wisdom and exorcise

00:04:14.290 --> 00:04:16.120 align:middle line:90%
those demons, so to speak.

00:04:16.120 --> 00:04:17.959 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, as you
read in my book,

00:04:17.959 --> 00:04:21.079 align:middle line:84%
one of the toughest
moments was telling my son

00:04:21.079 --> 00:04:22.350 align:middle line:90%
because he was only four.

00:04:22.350 --> 00:04:25.386 align:middle line:84%
And he kept asking, you know,
when is Daddy coming home?

00:04:25.386 --> 00:04:27.260 align:middle line:84%
You know, aren't
the doctors going

00:04:27.260 --> 00:04:28.630 align:middle line:90%
to make Daddy's heart better?

00:04:28.630 --> 00:04:32.800 align:middle line:84%
And I just couldn't spit
out the word dead at first.

00:04:32.800 --> 00:04:34.190 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Not that
he would comprehend.

00:04:34.190 --> 00:04:35.623 align:middle line:84%
No, not that a
four-year-old understands--

00:04:35.623 --> 00:04:37.200 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Yeah.
---dead.

00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:40.350 align:middle line:84%
So I told him again and again
Daddy's not coming home.

00:04:40.350 --> 00:04:45.090 align:middle line:84%
And I think that day-- you know,
the 24 hours after my husband

00:04:45.090 --> 00:04:48.080 align:middle line:84%
died-- that actually the
death was horrific but telling

00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:51.430 align:middle line:84%
my beautiful four-year-old,
with so much hope in his eyes,

00:04:51.430 --> 00:04:52.960 align:middle line:84%
that Daddy wasn't
coming home, that was

00:04:52.960 --> 00:04:55.320 align:middle line:90%
like, ugh-- knife in my heart.

00:04:55.320 --> 00:04:57.320 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: So how did
you go through even

00:04:57.320 --> 00:05:02.100 align:middle line:84%
healing that process-- and
take him along with you?

00:05:02.100 --> 00:05:03.690 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: It was a journey.

00:05:03.690 --> 00:05:05.235 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Yes, it
didn't happen overnight.

00:05:05.235 --> 00:05:06.405 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: It
didn't happen overnight.

00:05:06.405 --> 00:05:07.050 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And that's
important, right there,

00:05:07.050 --> 00:05:08.400 align:middle line:90%
for people to understand.

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:09.590 align:middle line:90%
It is a process.

00:05:09.590 --> 00:05:10.660 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: It is a process.

00:05:10.660 --> 00:05:13.150 align:middle line:90%
Healing is a process.

00:05:13.150 --> 00:05:15.500 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Edward [INAUDIBLE] has
done extensive research.

00:05:15.500 --> 00:05:18.330 align:middle line:84%
And as you said in the
opening, people can typically

00:05:18.330 --> 00:05:19.580 align:middle line:90%
suffer five to eight years.

00:05:19.580 --> 00:05:23.030 align:middle line:84%
And my life's work now is
to change that because I

00:05:23.030 --> 00:05:25.430 align:middle line:84%
think it takes five to
eight years because we

00:05:25.430 --> 00:05:26.210 align:middle line:90%
don't know any better.

00:05:26.210 --> 00:05:28.800 align:middle line:84%
It's not people's fault.
They don't have a recipe.

00:05:28.800 --> 00:05:31.230 align:middle line:84%
They don't have a system,
and they just wait.

00:05:31.230 --> 00:05:33.890 align:middle line:84%
But just as if you
had a broken arm,

00:05:33.890 --> 00:05:35.520 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't make sense
with a broken arm

00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:37.230 align:middle line:84%
to ask, well, how
long should I wait

00:05:37.230 --> 00:05:38.730 align:middle line:90%
before going to see the doctor?

00:05:38.730 --> 00:05:40.490 align:middle line:84%
But people ask that
with a broken heart--

00:05:40.490 --> 00:05:42.640 align:middle line:84%
like, how long should I
wait before doing anything?

00:05:42.640 --> 00:05:43.410 align:middle line:90%
Don't wait!

00:05:43.410 --> 00:05:44.130 align:middle line:90%
Do something now.

00:05:44.130 --> 00:05:45.800 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Don't,
like- do what though?

00:05:45.800 --> 00:05:46.600 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah, OK.

00:05:46.600 --> 00:05:48.510 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: I mean,
grieving groups,

00:05:48.510 --> 00:05:50.110 align:middle line:90%
processes, things like that?

00:05:50.110 --> 00:05:52.740 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah, well,
you know, I have a process.

00:05:52.740 --> 00:05:55.147 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to go
into that in depth.

00:05:55.147 --> 00:05:56.780 align:middle line:84%
And I'd love to share that
because it's something

00:05:56.780 --> 00:05:58.790 align:middle line:90%
people can immediately do.

00:05:58.790 --> 00:06:00.010 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: There
was a moment that I

00:06:00.010 --> 00:06:02.130 align:middle line:84%
read about that
you had that was--

00:06:02.130 --> 00:06:04.170 align:middle line:84%
it was a dream, wasn't it?
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:06:04.170 --> 00:06:07.440 align:middle line:84%
A moment of acceptance, which--
how long after your husband

00:06:07.440 --> 00:06:09.110 align:middle line:84%
passed did you have
that-- that dream?

00:06:09.110 --> 00:06:11.050 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: I had
a life-changing dream

00:06:11.050 --> 00:06:13.800 align:middle line:84%
on the second
anniversary of his death.

00:06:13.800 --> 00:06:17.080 align:middle line:84%
And up until that moment,
I still felt like a victim.

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:19.190 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I shouldn't
be a single mom.

00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:22.920 align:middle line:84%
I shouldn't, you
know, be a widow-- uh,

00:06:22.920 --> 00:06:25.230 align:middle line:90%
horrible word to even get out.

00:06:25.230 --> 00:06:27.730 align:middle line:84%
And our son shouldn't
be without his father.

00:06:27.730 --> 00:06:30.220 align:middle line:84%
And so my late husband
came to me in this dream,

00:06:30.220 --> 00:06:33.880 align:middle line:84%
and he asked me three questions,
and they changed my life.

00:06:33.880 --> 00:06:37.260 align:middle line:84%
The first question was, if you
had it to do all over again,

00:06:37.260 --> 00:06:38.320 align:middle line:90%
would you still marry me?

00:06:38.320 --> 00:06:39.020 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Oh.

00:06:39.020 --> 00:06:40.219 align:middle line:84%
I thought about
all the good times,

00:06:40.219 --> 00:06:43.380 align:middle line:90%
I'm, like, I'd still marry you.

00:06:43.380 --> 00:06:44.710 align:middle line:90%
The second question was--

00:06:44.710 --> 00:06:46.360 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: That's
powerful right there.

00:06:46.360 --> 00:06:46.635 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:06:46.635 --> 00:06:47.500 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: I'm
fighting back tears.

00:06:47.500 --> 00:06:48.499 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: I can see that.

00:06:48.499 --> 00:06:50.380 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: But I
mean, for you to even

00:06:50.380 --> 00:06:53.860 align:middle line:84%
get to that point of would you
go through this all over again?

00:06:53.860 --> 00:06:56.840 align:middle line:84%
And that you loved him that
much that you would go through

00:06:56.840 --> 00:06:58.662 align:middle line:84%
that all over again is huge.
Yeah.

00:06:58.662 --> 00:07:00.110 align:middle line:84%
That's beautiful.
Yeah.

00:07:00.110 --> 00:07:02.030 align:middle line:90%
And, OK, you got me.

00:07:02.030 --> 00:07:05.930 align:middle line:84%
And it was wonderful to get
those questions in the dream.

00:07:05.930 --> 00:07:09.920 align:middle line:84%
The second question was, if you
had it to do all over again,

00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:11.930 align:middle line:84%
would you still have our son?
LISA GARR: Oh.

00:07:11.930 --> 00:07:15.080 align:middle line:84%
And it was, like, of course,
he's the light of my life.

00:07:15.080 --> 00:07:16.210 align:middle line:90%
He's my joy-- my blessing.

00:07:16.210 --> 00:07:17.580 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't trade
him for anything.

00:07:17.580 --> 00:07:18.570 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: No.

00:07:18.570 --> 00:07:20.950 align:middle line:84%
And the third question
really changed my life

00:07:20.950 --> 00:07:24.070 align:middle line:84%
because he said, well,
given those two answers,

00:07:24.070 --> 00:07:27.710 align:middle line:84%
would you want to know
that I would die young?

00:07:27.710 --> 00:07:32.010 align:middle line:84%
And I searched my heart in the
dream for a very long moment.

00:07:32.010 --> 00:07:34.490 align:middle line:84%
And I discovered
the answer was no.

00:07:34.490 --> 00:07:37.050 align:middle line:84%
I would not want
to taint the joy

00:07:37.050 --> 00:07:39.157 align:middle line:90%
that we did have with dread.

00:07:39.157 --> 00:07:40.090 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: That makes sense.

00:07:40.090 --> 00:07:42.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, every moment
you would be--

00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:43.190 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Dreading it.
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:07:43.190 --> 00:07:43.460 align:middle line:90%
Hm mm.

00:07:43.460 --> 00:07:44.893 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: And that
changed everything.

00:07:44.893 --> 00:07:46.910 align:middle line:84%
And it allowed
that victim energy

00:07:46.910 --> 00:07:51.190 align:middle line:84%
to just evaporate and be
replaced with gratitude

00:07:51.190 --> 00:07:53.230 align:middle line:90%
for the time that we did have.

00:07:53.230 --> 00:07:55.840 align:middle line:84%
And for those first
two years, you know,

00:07:55.840 --> 00:07:57.480 align:middle line:90%
grief is not one emotion.

00:07:57.480 --> 00:07:59.196 align:middle line:84%
It's a cacophony of emotions.
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:07:59.196 --> 00:08:01.095 align:middle line:84%
And you read in my book,
"From Heartbreak to Happiness."

00:08:01.095 --> 00:08:01.794 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:08:01.794 --> 00:08:06.410 align:middle line:84%
But I did in general have a
lot of victim energy around it.

00:08:06.410 --> 00:08:09.480 align:middle line:84%
But after that dream, that
sense of being a victim

00:08:09.480 --> 00:08:10.385 align:middle line:90%
permanently evaporated.

00:08:10.385 --> 00:08:12.550 align:middle line:10%
LISA GARR: Well, I want
to expand on those two

00:08:12.550 --> 00:08:15.730 align:middle line:10%
years for a second because you
do an amazing job of putting

00:08:15.730 --> 00:08:18.410 align:middle line:10%
words to those feelings
that people are having about

00:08:18.410 --> 00:08:23.180 align:middle line:10%
their joy being taken away--
about the victimization of it

00:08:23.180 --> 00:08:27.350 align:middle line:10%
shouldn't be this way--
of are they in pain--

00:08:27.350 --> 00:08:29.417 align:middle line:10%
all of that, any kind of loss.
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:08:29.417 --> 00:08:30.550 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: As I
mentioned earlier,

00:08:30.550 --> 00:08:32.090 align:middle line:90%
it could be the loss of a job.

00:08:32.090 --> 00:08:34.501 align:middle line:84%
It could be explaining the
loss of a pet to a little one.

00:08:34.501 --> 00:08:36.409 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.
LISA GARR: Yeah, all right, so--

00:08:36.409 --> 00:08:38.690 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Well, I really
define grief as the loss

00:08:38.690 --> 00:08:40.530 align:middle line:90%
of hopes and dreams.

00:08:40.530 --> 00:08:42.020 align:middle line:90%
So it doesn't have to be death.

00:08:42.020 --> 00:08:43.971 align:middle line:84%
You know, a divorce
has got grief--

00:08:43.971 --> 00:08:44.670 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:08:44.670 --> 00:08:46.160 align:middle line:84%
---because of the loss
of hopes and dreams.

00:08:46.160 --> 00:08:46.859 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:08:46.859 --> 00:08:49.370 align:middle line:84%
If you lose or change
careers, there can be grief.

00:08:49.370 --> 00:08:52.870 align:middle line:84%
Financial loss grief--
having a special needs child

00:08:52.870 --> 00:08:55.420 align:middle line:84%
with autism, I also define
that as the loss of hopes

00:08:55.420 --> 00:08:56.714 align:middle line:90%
and dreams, so there's grief.

00:08:56.714 --> 00:08:57.480 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Interesting.

00:08:57.480 --> 00:09:00.660 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, I define grief very,
very broadly because it's

00:09:00.660 --> 00:09:01.890 align:middle line:90%
not what happens exactly.

00:09:01.890 --> 00:09:03.580 align:middle line:84%
It's what did you
expect to happen?

00:09:03.580 --> 00:09:04.660 align:middle line:90%
What were your hopes and dreams?

00:09:04.660 --> 00:09:08.470 align:middle line:84%
And then, if you just
allow your dreams

00:09:08.470 --> 00:09:11.680 align:middle line:84%
to be stillborn without honoring
that and processing that

00:09:11.680 --> 00:09:13.400 align:middle line:84%
somehow, it's going
to weigh on you--

00:09:13.400 --> 00:09:17.130 align:middle line:84%
whereas if you acknowledge
that, then you can grieve it.

00:09:17.130 --> 00:09:19.740 align:middle line:84%
And then there opens
a space for new dreams

00:09:19.740 --> 00:09:21.330 align:middle line:90%
and new possibilities.

00:09:21.330 --> 00:09:23.476 align:middle line:84%
But coming back
to your question--

00:09:23.476 --> 00:09:24.576 align:middle line:84%
or did you want
to say something?

00:09:24.576 --> 00:09:25.842 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Yeah,
well, it was actually

00:09:25.842 --> 00:09:28.600 align:middle line:84%
that-- what you just said about
having a child with autism.

00:09:28.600 --> 00:09:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And I heard somebody
from your-- that

00:09:31.460 --> 00:09:33.780 align:middle line:84%
had been through your
workshops and your process

00:09:33.780 --> 00:09:37.340 align:middle line:84%
explain that was her experience
of when she found out

00:09:37.340 --> 00:09:41.070 align:middle line:84%
her child had autism,
that she really

00:09:41.070 --> 00:09:44.221 align:middle line:84%
felt like she was robbed from
having a normal child, right?

00:09:44.221 --> 00:09:45.820 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.
LISA GARR: That experience.

00:09:45.820 --> 00:09:49.510 align:middle line:84%
She had a life-changing
"aha" at one of my Grief

00:09:49.510 --> 00:09:50.360 align:middle line:90%
Coach Academy workshops.

00:09:50.360 --> 00:09:53.240 align:middle line:84%
And she went from thinking
that her special needs daughter

00:09:53.240 --> 00:09:57.040 align:middle line:84%
was driving her
insane to realizing

00:09:57.040 --> 00:09:59.400 align:middle line:84%
that she was driving her sane.
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:02.630 align:middle line:84%
And that was really calling
her forth into her greatness,

00:10:02.630 --> 00:10:04.450 align:middle line:84%
into being grounded,
into being peaceful,

00:10:04.450 --> 00:10:06.680 align:middle line:84%
into being the best
human being and mother

00:10:06.680 --> 00:10:08.300 align:middle line:90%
she could possibly be.

00:10:08.300 --> 00:10:11.010 align:middle line:84%
And she's shifted from
feeling like this shouldn't be

00:10:11.010 --> 00:10:13.880 align:middle line:84%
happening to me, like--
to feeling like gratitude

00:10:13.880 --> 00:10:15.405 align:middle line:90%
and it changed her life.

00:10:15.405 --> 00:10:16.804 align:middle line:84%
So in a moment,
[SNAPS]

00:10:16.804 --> 00:10:18.080 align:middle line:90%
---we can change our thinking.

00:10:18.080 --> 00:10:20.980 align:middle line:84%
And it's our thinking that
keeps us stuck in grief.

00:10:20.980 --> 00:10:24.020 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Do you think we have
to go through a two-year period

00:10:24.020 --> 00:10:25.140 align:middle line:84%
before we get there?
AURORA WINTER: No!

00:10:25.140 --> 00:10:25.926 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: No?

00:10:25.926 --> 00:10:26.820 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: No.

00:10:26.820 --> 00:10:29.687 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: I mean, 30
minutes, Aurora-- really?

00:10:29.687 --> 00:10:30.950 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Really.
-Really.

00:10:30.950 --> 00:10:31.683 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Really.

00:10:31.683 --> 00:10:34.870 align:middle line:84%
And here's-- when
I coach people,

00:10:34.870 --> 00:10:38.030 align:middle line:84%
they can sometimes have
a meaningful but welcome

00:10:38.030 --> 00:10:39.310 align:middle line:90%
shift in 30 minutes.

00:10:39.310 --> 00:10:41.800 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes they have
a life-changing shift

00:10:41.800 --> 00:10:43.740 align:middle line:90%
in 30 minutes or less.

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:46.610 align:middle line:84%
And just like you
can get totally clean

00:10:46.610 --> 00:10:49.070 align:middle line:84%
and have a luxurious
shower in 30 minutes,

00:10:49.070 --> 00:10:50.870 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't mean that
you only do it once.

00:10:50.870 --> 00:10:51.910 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And you're not
going to get dirty again.

00:10:51.910 --> 00:10:52.580 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Right.
LISA GARR: Exactly.

00:10:52.580 --> 00:10:53.890 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: So
the same with grief.

00:10:53.890 --> 00:10:56.480 align:middle line:84%
If you're really in
the midst of something,

00:10:56.480 --> 00:10:59.860 align:middle line:84%
do the peace method
every day for 30 minutes

00:10:59.860 --> 00:11:02.410 align:middle line:84%
until you get peaceful--
until you feel grounded.

00:11:02.410 --> 00:11:03.890 align:middle line:84%
It's something you
can do at home.

00:11:03.890 --> 00:11:05.740 align:middle line:84%
You can do it as a
journaling process.

00:11:05.740 --> 00:11:07.700 align:middle line:84%
But if you're really in
the depths of despair,

00:11:07.700 --> 00:11:09.360 align:middle line:84%
it's going to work
better if you come

00:11:09.360 --> 00:11:11.890 align:middle line:84%
to a workshop or work with
a certified grief coach,

00:11:11.890 --> 00:11:12.790 align:middle line:90%
obviously.

00:11:12.790 --> 00:11:15.250 align:middle line:84%
But 30 minutes a day
will change your life.

00:11:15.250 --> 00:11:16.050 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: That's great.

00:11:16.050 --> 00:11:18.390 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to be teaching
that in just a little bit.

00:11:18.390 --> 00:11:21.550 align:middle line:84%
But so if somebody
would start off though

00:11:21.550 --> 00:11:24.990 align:middle line:84%
after they're fresh after
having somebody leave

00:11:24.990 --> 00:11:28.880 align:middle line:84%
their lives that they love
or a situation or a job,

00:11:28.880 --> 00:11:31.237 align:middle line:84%
would you recommend starting
with the journaling process?

00:11:31.237 --> 00:11:33.270 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: I would recommend
starting with the journaling

00:11:33.270 --> 00:11:36.640 align:middle line:84%
process and really
allowing all-- just to vent

00:11:36.640 --> 00:11:39.660 align:middle line:84%
those feelings because I
think unexpressed feelings are

00:11:39.660 --> 00:11:41.370 align:middle line:90%
like food poisoning.

00:11:41.370 --> 00:11:43.131 align:middle line:84%
And if you keep the
food poison inside

00:11:43.131 --> 00:11:44.530 align:middle line:84%
because you want to
stuff it-- because you

00:11:44.530 --> 00:11:46.680 align:middle line:84%
know it's going to be a
little bit messy, it's toxic.

00:11:46.680 --> 00:11:48.270 align:middle line:90%
So journaling is easy.

00:11:48.270 --> 00:11:50.320 align:middle line:84%
It's cheap-- all you need is
a pen and a piece of paper.

00:11:50.320 --> 00:11:52.480 align:middle line:84%
And you can really
discover a lot.

00:11:52.480 --> 00:11:54.330 align:middle line:90%
I learned so much.

00:11:54.330 --> 00:11:56.920 align:middle line:84%
And I-- and I got
so much of my energy

00:11:56.920 --> 00:11:59.557 align:middle line:84%
out by writing it down--
and later became the book,

00:11:59.557 --> 00:12:00.590 align:middle line:90%
"From Heartbreak to Happiness."

00:12:00.590 --> 00:12:03.430 align:middle line:84%
But I never intended
even to reread it myself

00:12:03.430 --> 00:12:04.570 align:middle line:90%
when I was writing it.

00:12:04.570 --> 00:12:05.970 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Some
people don't know

00:12:05.970 --> 00:12:08.020 align:middle line:84%
the scale-- the
level that they're

00:12:08.020 --> 00:12:09.360 align:middle line:90%
at in terms of grieving.

00:12:09.360 --> 00:12:11.160 align:middle line:84%
And you've basically
put that together

00:12:11.160 --> 00:12:14.940 align:middle line:84%
in kind of a grief wheel to
show people kind of to wake

00:12:14.940 --> 00:12:17.531 align:middle line:84%
up to where they are on
the grieving scale, right?

00:12:17.531 --> 00:12:19.230 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yes.
LISA GARR: It's a great idea.

00:12:19.230 --> 00:12:21.210 align:middle line:10%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah,
the grief relief wheel

00:12:21.210 --> 00:12:24.890 align:middle line:10%
is a wonderful thing so
that you can see at a glance

00:12:24.890 --> 00:12:28.000 align:middle line:10%
where your life is off
balance, and you can

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:29.860 align:middle line:10%
see what you can do about it.

00:12:29.860 --> 00:12:33.130 align:middle line:10%
So just like you want a wheel in
your car to be nice and round,

00:12:33.130 --> 00:12:36.420 align:middle line:10%
you want your life to
be nice and rounded.

00:12:36.420 --> 00:12:40.530 align:middle line:84%
And people who are in grief tend
to-- even more than normal--

00:12:40.530 --> 00:12:43.050 align:middle line:84%
go to their strong suits
and ignore their weak suits.

00:12:43.050 --> 00:12:45.430 align:middle line:90%
So they can get very lopsided.

00:12:45.430 --> 00:12:46.960 align:middle line:90%
And so it just encourages you.

00:12:46.960 --> 00:12:49.770 align:middle line:84%
And it's something very simple
that people can do on their own

00:12:49.770 --> 00:12:52.500 align:middle line:84%
or they can do with a coach
and help them see what to do--

00:12:52.500 --> 00:12:54.840 align:middle line:90%
what specific action to take.

00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:57.100 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: We're going to take
a look at a video that explains

00:12:57.100 --> 00:12:58.767 align:middle line:90%
the grief wheel a little bit.

00:12:58.767 --> 00:13:00.600 align:middle line:84%
And then, you can explain a
little bit more after that.

00:13:00.600 --> 00:13:03.110 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look at this.

00:13:03.110 --> 00:13:04.630 align:middle line:10%
So what is the Grief Wheel?

00:13:04.630 --> 00:13:05.930 align:middle line:10%
Here's what it looks like.

00:13:05.930 --> 00:13:09.950 align:middle line:10%
It's just a circle, and it shows
you-- it's a self-rating thing.

00:13:09.950 --> 00:13:11.560 align:middle line:10%
You can do this
every day, and you

00:13:11.560 --> 00:13:15.830 align:middle line:10%
look at how do you rate
yourself on a scale of 1 to 10

00:13:15.830 --> 00:13:18.060 align:middle line:10%
in these various areas?

00:13:18.060 --> 00:13:19.780 align:middle line:10%
So let me just talk
you through it.

00:13:19.780 --> 00:13:21.030 align:middle line:10%
So there's no wrong or right.

00:13:21.030 --> 00:13:22.810 align:middle line:90%
It's just a matter of clarity.

00:13:22.810 --> 00:13:25.440 align:middle line:84%
So when you do this
Grief Wheel every day,

00:13:25.440 --> 00:13:28.360 align:middle line:84%
you'll rate yourself
on a scale of 1 to 10

00:13:28.360 --> 00:13:32.590 align:middle line:84%
on Acceptance and Forgiveness,
on Self-expression,

00:13:32.590 --> 00:13:37.710 align:middle line:84%
on Spiritual Connection, on
Support Systems, on Self Care,

00:13:37.710 --> 00:13:41.450 align:middle line:84%
on Finance and Legal, on
Career and Profession,

00:13:41.450 --> 00:13:45.000 align:middle line:84%
on Family and Parenting,
on Physical Activity,

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:47.850 align:middle line:84%
and on Maintaining
Daily Routine.

00:13:47.850 --> 00:13:50.190 align:middle line:90%
It's just a snapshot in time.

00:13:50.190 --> 00:13:52.660 align:middle line:84%
So it can change
from day to day.

00:13:52.660 --> 00:13:55.540 align:middle line:84%
And also the good thing
is, as you take activities

00:13:55.540 --> 00:13:58.230 align:middle line:84%
and you do this every
day for the next 30 days,

00:13:58.230 --> 00:14:01.950 align:middle line:84%
you gradually take
small steps to increase

00:14:01.950 --> 00:14:03.180 align:middle line:90%
the numbers that are low.

00:14:03.180 --> 00:14:06.400 align:middle line:84%
You'll find that your wheel
changes very dramatically.

00:14:06.400 --> 00:14:09.690 align:middle line:84%
And your peace, your
productivity, your ability

00:14:09.690 --> 00:14:12.170 align:middle line:84%
to deal with the
challenge also changes

00:14:12.170 --> 00:14:14.220 align:middle line:90%
and increases dramatically.

00:14:14.220 --> 00:14:16.370 align:middle line:90%
Let's look at an example.

00:14:16.370 --> 00:14:18.740 align:middle line:10%
This is for a mother
who's got a special needs

00:14:18.740 --> 00:14:20.110 align:middle line:10%
child with autism.

00:14:20.110 --> 00:14:22.050 align:middle line:10%
She's dealing with
that diagnosis.

00:14:22.050 --> 00:14:25.120 align:middle line:10%
This is something new for her,
and this is what her Grief

00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:26.620 align:middle line:10%
Wheel might look like.

00:14:26.620 --> 00:14:29.360 align:middle line:84%
And again, this is something
she'd do every day for 30 days,

00:14:29.360 --> 00:14:31.450 align:middle line:90%
so it would change over time.

00:14:31.450 --> 00:14:32.890 align:middle line:90%
Here's what it looks like.

00:14:32.890 --> 00:14:35.070 align:middle line:10%
And as you can see if this
was a wheel on your car,

00:14:35.070 --> 00:14:37.430 align:middle line:10%
your car would not
be running smoothly.

00:14:37.430 --> 00:14:40.090 align:middle line:84%
And the same way when this
is a wheel on your life,

00:14:40.090 --> 00:14:42.320 align:middle line:84%
your life is not
running so smoothly.

00:14:42.320 --> 00:14:45.460 align:middle line:84%
So let's see how she could use
the Grief Wheel to get her life

00:14:45.460 --> 00:14:47.250 align:middle line:84%
in greater balance
and get everything

00:14:47.250 --> 00:14:48.870 align:middle line:90%
running much more smoothly.

00:14:48.870 --> 00:14:49.570 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:14:49.570 --> 00:14:51.440 align:middle line:10%
So she's given the
self-assessment,

00:14:51.440 --> 00:14:53.800 align:middle line:10%
and this again is just
a snapshot in time

00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:56.130 align:middle line:10%
how she is doing today.

00:14:56.130 --> 00:14:57.190 align:middle line:90%
Tomorrow could be different.

00:14:57.190 --> 00:14:59.050 align:middle line:84%
A month from now
will be different

00:14:59.050 --> 00:15:00.600 align:middle line:90%
if she does this every day.

00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:05.010 align:middle line:10%
So she's given herself an 8 on
Acceptance and Forgiveness, a 3

00:15:05.010 --> 00:15:09.875 align:middle line:10%
on Self-expression, a 9 on
Spiritual Connection, a 2

00:15:09.875 --> 00:15:16.250 align:middle line:10%
on Support Systems, a 5 on Self
Care, a 7 on Finance and Legal,

00:15:16.250 --> 00:15:21.870 align:middle line:10%
a 5 on Career and Profession, a
5 on Family and Parenting, a 9

00:15:21.870 --> 00:15:24.380 align:middle line:10%
on physical activity-- she's
a marathon runner so she's

00:15:24.380 --> 00:15:27.760 align:middle line:10%
getting a lot of
activity there-- and a 7

00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.780 align:middle line:10%
on Maintaining a Daily Routine.

00:15:29.780 --> 00:15:30.480 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:15:30.480 --> 00:15:33.780 align:middle line:84%
So when she looks at this
Grief Wheel, what stands out?

00:15:33.780 --> 00:15:38.110 align:middle line:84%
OK, what stands out, of course,
is the low score of only a 2

00:15:38.110 --> 00:15:42.960 align:middle line:84%
on Support Systems and only
a 3 on Self-expression.

00:15:42.960 --> 00:15:45.280 align:middle line:90%
So what would plus 2 look like?

00:15:45.280 --> 00:15:46.705 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to
look necessarily

00:15:46.705 --> 00:15:48.750 align:middle line:84%
at what a 10 in
Support Systems would

00:15:48.750 --> 00:15:51.510 align:middle line:84%
be like, but just go
for an easy peasy step

00:15:51.510 --> 00:15:53.270 align:middle line:90%
that she can do today.

00:15:53.270 --> 00:15:56.840 align:middle line:10%
So to go from a 2 in
Support Systems to a 4

00:15:56.840 --> 00:16:00.820 align:middle line:10%
on Support Systems for her
could look like that today,

00:16:00.820 --> 00:16:04.700 align:middle line:10%
she'll just make a plan for
what the perfect Support System

00:16:04.700 --> 00:16:06.690 align:middle line:10%
scenario might look like.

00:16:06.690 --> 00:16:10.340 align:middle line:10%
She might not actually even need
to take any action on it today.

00:16:10.340 --> 00:16:12.050 align:middle line:10%
Maybe she'll do that tomorrow.

00:16:12.050 --> 00:16:15.380 align:middle line:10%
But today, she could feel
like a 4 in Support Systems

00:16:15.380 --> 00:16:19.050 align:middle line:10%
as she gets more clear where
she could hire more support

00:16:19.050 --> 00:16:20.520 align:middle line:10%
or ask for more support.

00:16:20.520 --> 00:16:24.350 align:middle line:84%
Whatever crisis, heartbreak,
or stress you are dealing with,

00:16:24.350 --> 00:16:27.080 align:middle line:84%
this tool will be very
helpful for you to get

00:16:27.080 --> 00:16:28.820 align:middle line:90%
your life back in balance.

00:16:28.820 --> 00:16:32.020 align:middle line:84%
I promise you, if you use this
every day for the next 30 days,

00:16:32.020 --> 00:16:36.170 align:middle line:84%
it will change your life and
increase your sense of peace,

00:16:36.170 --> 00:16:39.060 align:middle line:90%
productivity, and clarity.

00:16:39.060 --> 00:16:40.210 align:middle line:90%
Great, great tool.

00:16:40.210 --> 00:16:41.690 align:middle line:84%
So let's go into
this a little bit.

00:16:41.690 --> 00:16:44.720 align:middle line:84%
So this is basically like
taking a self-assessment, like

00:16:44.720 --> 00:16:45.840 align:middle line:90%
being your own grief coach--

00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:47.790 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Like being your
own grief coach-- exactly.

00:16:47.790 --> 00:16:51.360 align:middle line:84%
---to see where you're at on the
scale every single day in these

00:16:51.360 --> 00:16:53.010 align:middle line:90%
various different segments.

00:16:53.010 --> 00:16:55.090 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah, and
it's nice to give yourself,

00:16:55.090 --> 00:16:57.490 align:middle line:84%
you know, thumbs up-- you know,
we're doing 8 on something.

00:16:57.490 --> 00:17:01.320 align:middle line:10%
But also just don't try to
stretch from a 2 or 3 to a 10,

00:17:01.320 --> 00:17:04.790 align:middle line:10%
but just do something easy
peasy and make it manageable.

00:17:04.790 --> 00:17:07.204 align:middle line:10%
And then just check it
every day for 30 days

00:17:07.204 --> 00:17:09.170 align:middle line:10%
and just be gentle
with yourself.

00:17:09.170 --> 00:17:11.790 align:middle line:10%
Be kind to yourself is very key
when you're dealing with grief.

00:17:11.790 --> 00:17:15.250 align:middle line:10%
And yet if you take a little bit
of action every day, gradually

00:17:15.250 --> 00:17:18.250 align:middle line:10%
you'll get those lower
numbers much higher.

00:17:18.250 --> 00:17:22.700 align:middle line:84%
For example, in the first 100
days of my husband's death,

00:17:22.700 --> 00:17:23.981 align:middle line:84%
you know, I was
really shattered--

00:17:23.981 --> 00:17:24.680 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:17:24.680 --> 00:17:26.560 align:middle line:84%
---using the British
sense of the word.

00:17:26.560 --> 00:17:28.369 align:middle line:90%
I was really in deep grief.

00:17:28.369 --> 00:17:33.470 align:middle line:84%
And, uh, I finally went to
see a coach or a therapist

00:17:33.470 --> 00:17:34.960 align:middle line:84%
because I just
couldn't handle it.

00:17:34.960 --> 00:17:38.500 align:middle line:84%
Every night when I fell
asleep, I would again and again

00:17:38.500 --> 00:17:40.140 align:middle line:90%
see him dying in front of me.

00:17:40.140 --> 00:17:41.077 align:middle line:90%
And I lost 15 pounds.

00:17:41.077 --> 00:17:41.910 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: It's shocking.

00:17:41.910 --> 00:17:43.309 align:middle line:84%
I was haggard.
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:17:43.309 --> 00:17:44.040 align:middle line:90%
Hm mm.

00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:45.540 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: I mean,
post traumatic stress.

00:17:45.540 --> 00:17:46.360 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Absolutely.

00:17:46.360 --> 00:17:50.190 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: So they, uh--
my acceptance was not-- was,

00:17:50.190 --> 00:17:52.430 align:middle line:90%
you know, 2.

00:17:52.430 --> 00:17:55.890 align:middle line:84%
The therapist said-- I said you
have to make these dreams stop.

00:17:55.890 --> 00:17:57.590 align:middle line:84%
I cannot deal with
these nightmares.

00:17:57.590 --> 00:17:59.300 align:middle line:90%
I just-- I couldn't sleep.

00:17:59.300 --> 00:18:00.110 align:middle line:90%
I was haggard.

00:18:00.110 --> 00:18:01.260 align:middle line:90%
I was a mom.

00:18:01.260 --> 00:18:03.300 align:middle line:90%
I needed to get my act together.

00:18:03.300 --> 00:18:06.401 align:middle line:84%
And the coach said to me,
well, tell me a little bit more

00:18:06.401 --> 00:18:08.350 align:middle line:84%
about your life.
I'm like, I just want results.

00:18:08.350 --> 00:18:09.130 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to cry.

00:18:09.130 --> 00:18:10.822 align:middle line:84%
Just make the
dreams stop, please.

00:18:10.822 --> 00:18:12.240 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:18:12.240 --> 00:18:13.676 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
you know, tell me

00:18:13.676 --> 00:18:14.800 align:middle line:90%
a little bit about your life.

00:18:14.800 --> 00:18:15.910 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:18:15.910 --> 00:18:18.300 align:middle line:84%
I said, my husband
died a few months ago.

00:18:18.300 --> 00:18:19.730 align:middle line:84%
How are you getting
through the day?

00:18:19.730 --> 00:18:22.130 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, I just pretend
he's away on a business trip.

00:18:22.130 --> 00:18:25.200 align:middle line:84%
And then I get
through the day OK.

00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:27.590 align:middle line:84%
And she's like, so you
get through the day

00:18:27.590 --> 00:18:29.700 align:middle line:84%
by pretending that he's
away on a business trip?

00:18:29.700 --> 00:18:31.790 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, yeah,
what's it to you?

00:18:31.790 --> 00:18:33.800 align:middle line:84%
She's like, well,
maybe the dreams--

00:18:33.800 --> 00:18:36.660 align:middle line:84%
maybe the nightmares
aren't the problem.

00:18:36.660 --> 00:18:39.830 align:middle line:84%
Maybe they're the solution
because they're calling you

00:18:39.830 --> 00:18:43.200 align:middle line:90%
to accept what is the reality.

00:18:43.200 --> 00:18:45.120 align:middle line:84%
He's not away on
a business trip.

00:18:45.120 --> 00:18:46.520 align:middle line:90%
You know, he's dead.

00:18:46.520 --> 00:18:50.425 align:middle line:84%
So that one coaching
session shifted me from a 2

00:18:50.425 --> 00:18:53.360 align:middle line:84%
on Acceptance to,
you know, an 8.

00:18:53.360 --> 00:18:56.220 align:middle line:84%
So it can happen quite
quickly but just to notice

00:18:56.220 --> 00:18:57.660 align:middle line:90%
where you are.

00:18:57.660 --> 00:19:00.150 align:middle line:84%
It might be something you need
somebody to coach you through.

00:19:00.150 --> 00:19:02.380 align:middle line:84%
Or with the example that
we just had on that video,

00:19:02.380 --> 00:19:04.980 align:middle line:84%
it could be as simple
as taking some action

00:19:04.980 --> 00:19:07.090 align:middle line:90%
to get more support system.

00:19:07.090 --> 00:19:08.820 align:middle line:84%
So small things
that you can do can

00:19:08.820 --> 00:19:11.070 align:middle line:84%
really make a big
difference in getting

00:19:11.070 --> 00:19:12.530 align:middle line:90%
your life back in balance.

00:19:12.530 --> 00:19:15.460 align:middle line:84%
It seems like that these
are steps that you--

00:19:15.460 --> 00:19:17.340 align:middle line:84%
that just one by
one, sometimes you

00:19:17.340 --> 00:19:18.840 align:middle line:90%
go eight rungs up the ladder.

00:19:18.840 --> 00:19:20.570 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes you drop back three.

00:19:20.570 --> 00:19:22.100 align:middle line:90%
And it's a process.

00:19:22.100 --> 00:19:23.610 align:middle line:84%
But when you have
tangible things

00:19:23.610 --> 00:19:25.020 align:middle line:84%
you have to deal
with, for example,

00:19:25.020 --> 00:19:30.000 align:middle line:84%
finances and the paperwork
and the details and so

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:34.080 align:middle line:84%
forth of-- yeah, it gets to
be-- I mean, not only are you

00:19:34.080 --> 00:19:36.090 align:middle line:84%
dealing with a huge
amount of emotions

00:19:36.090 --> 00:19:38.800 align:middle line:90%
but you have all of that stuff.

00:19:38.800 --> 00:19:39.900 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER:
This is where it's

00:19:39.900 --> 00:19:41.810 align:middle line:90%
so helpful not to do it alone.

00:19:41.810 --> 00:19:43.840 align:middle line:10%
I think kindness is key.

00:19:43.840 --> 00:19:47.010 align:middle line:10%
And the second thing
people need is connection.

00:19:47.010 --> 00:19:52.080 align:middle line:10%
So connection, too, might be
a finance, legal, bookkeeper,

00:19:52.080 --> 00:19:53.850 align:middle line:10%
might be a coach,
might be a friend,

00:19:53.850 --> 00:19:57.020 align:middle line:10%
might be a spiritual advisor--
whatever is the weak link.

00:19:57.020 --> 00:19:59.020 align:middle line:84%
Because it's interesting
that you say that.

00:19:59.020 --> 00:20:01.060 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I studied
honors economics.

00:20:01.060 --> 00:20:03.340 align:middle line:90%
I come from a family of PhDs.

00:20:03.340 --> 00:20:06.060 align:middle line:84%
I wrote and designed
a tax shelter.

00:20:06.060 --> 00:20:08.570 align:middle line:84%
But after my husband died,
I could not pay the bills.

00:20:08.570 --> 00:20:10.370 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't understand it.

00:20:10.370 --> 00:20:13.850 align:middle line:84%
And actually, when you
have a really big trauma,

00:20:13.850 --> 00:20:15.391 align:middle line:84%
the dominant side of
your brain can switch.

00:20:15.391 --> 00:20:16.090 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Wow.

00:20:16.090 --> 00:20:20.120 align:middle line:84%
So I want the-- your audience
to know you're not going crazy.

00:20:20.120 --> 00:20:21.830 align:middle line:90%
It's not Alzheimer's.

00:20:21.830 --> 00:20:23.110 align:middle line:90%
This is temporary.

00:20:23.110 --> 00:20:27.300 align:middle line:84%
But one of the symptoms of
major trauma or deep grief

00:20:27.300 --> 00:20:29.790 align:middle line:84%
can be like you feel
like you're stupid.

00:20:29.790 --> 00:20:30.530 align:middle line:90%
You're not stupid.

00:20:30.530 --> 00:20:31.296 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Interesting.

00:20:31.296 --> 00:20:32.083 align:middle line:90%
You're just grieving.

00:20:32.083 --> 00:20:33.482 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Hm mm.
Absolutely.

00:20:33.482 --> 00:20:34.220 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:20:34.220 --> 00:20:39.010 align:middle line:84%
Is it common to dive into a
routine or of physicality--

00:20:39.010 --> 00:20:40.370 align:middle line:84%
like, I noticed
that you mentioned

00:20:40.370 --> 00:20:42.380 align:middle line:84%
you went into working--
I have a friend

00:20:42.380 --> 00:20:46.780 align:middle line:84%
who also is dealing with a very,
very rapid loss of her husband.

00:20:46.780 --> 00:20:49.310 align:middle line:84%
And she is in the gym
three to four hours a day,

00:20:49.310 --> 00:20:51.461 align:middle line:84%
just because it's something
that she can handle.

00:20:51.461 --> 00:20:53.590 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.
-Is that common?

00:20:53.590 --> 00:20:56.550 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: I think
it's common that whatever

00:20:56.550 --> 00:21:00.560 align:middle line:84%
is a strong thing for you--
that was working for you

00:21:00.560 --> 00:21:03.080 align:middle line:90%
before that you redouble that.

00:21:03.080 --> 00:21:05.900 align:middle line:84%
So for me, I was
already writing before.

00:21:05.900 --> 00:21:08.340 align:middle line:90%
It was a release for me before.

00:21:08.340 --> 00:21:10.220 align:middle line:84%
And I-- it was my
lifeline after he died.

00:21:10.220 --> 00:21:12.590 align:middle line:90%
I was already exercising before.

00:21:12.590 --> 00:21:14.060 align:middle line:90%
And so I redoubled that.

00:21:14.060 --> 00:21:15.810 align:middle line:84%
But where coaching
can come in handy

00:21:15.810 --> 00:21:18.760 align:middle line:84%
is that can make your life
even more lopsided sometimes

00:21:18.760 --> 00:21:20.930 align:middle line:84%
if you don't also
look at how are

00:21:20.930 --> 00:21:22.729 align:middle line:84%
we going to get the bills paid?
LISA GARR: Right.

00:21:22.729 --> 00:21:24.310 align:middle line:90%
Simple, practical things.

00:21:24.310 --> 00:21:25.280 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:21:25.280 --> 00:21:27.880 align:middle line:84%
And I really invite people,
especially the first three,

00:21:27.880 --> 00:21:30.210 align:middle line:90%
four months, be gentle with you.

00:21:30.210 --> 00:21:31.870 align:middle line:90%
Whatever you're doing, it's OK.

00:21:31.870 --> 00:21:34.315 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Is it OK if you
sit and stare at walls?

00:21:34.315 --> 00:21:35.117 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:21:35.117 --> 00:21:36.850 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: You might
not want to stare at walls.

00:21:36.850 --> 00:21:39.215 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's really good to
get outside, in the sunshine,

00:21:39.215 --> 00:21:43.190 align:middle line:84%
get some vitamin D, walk,
move, breathe, sleep.

00:21:43.190 --> 00:21:45.980 align:middle line:84%
But you know, I drank
after my husband died.

00:21:45.980 --> 00:21:47.120 align:middle line:90%
And I've never been a drinker.

00:21:47.120 --> 00:21:48.670 align:middle line:90%
It was only one beer a night.

00:21:48.670 --> 00:21:50.340 align:middle line:84%
But for me, it seemed
like I'm alcoholic.

00:21:50.340 --> 00:21:53.320 align:middle line:84%
But you know, it's
OK-- whatever you need.

00:21:53.320 --> 00:21:56.120 align:middle line:84%
But after, say,
maybe six months,

00:21:56.120 --> 00:21:58.860 align:middle line:84%
you really need to start
saying yes to life.

00:21:58.860 --> 00:22:01.610 align:middle line:84%
And-- and you can
use these processes

00:22:01.610 --> 00:22:03.830 align:middle line:84%
as a way to say yes to
life or work with a coach

00:22:03.830 --> 00:22:05.960 align:middle line:90%
or whatever it is for you.

00:22:05.960 --> 00:22:09.062 align:middle line:84%
Don't stay hanging out
too long in the dark

00:22:09.062 --> 00:22:10.190 align:middle line:90%
looking at the wall.

00:22:10.190 --> 00:22:12.280 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Well, it's great to
know that there's organizations

00:22:12.280 --> 00:22:13.900 align:middle line:90%
like yours that are out there.

00:22:13.900 --> 00:22:15.750 align:middle line:84%
Tell me about the
Grief Coach Academy.

00:22:15.750 --> 00:22:16.580 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:22:16.580 --> 00:22:17.520 align:middle line:90%
How did you start it?

00:22:17.520 --> 00:22:19.560 align:middle line:84%
How long after your husband
passed did you start that?

00:22:19.560 --> 00:22:20.660 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER:
Oh, it was quite--

00:22:20.660 --> 00:22:23.780 align:middle line:84%
my husband died a long time
ago now-- 20 years ago.

00:22:23.780 --> 00:22:26.980 align:middle line:84%
And I started the Grief
Coach Academy in 2006.

00:22:26.980 --> 00:22:28.730 align:middle line:84%
And it's like Oprah
says, sometimes you

00:22:28.730 --> 00:22:32.450 align:middle line:84%
choose your career, and
sometimes it chooses you.

00:22:32.450 --> 00:22:35.120 align:middle line:84%
And I'm really honored
and privileged to be

00:22:35.120 --> 00:22:39.380 align:middle line:84%
a catalyst for changing how
people think about grief

00:22:39.380 --> 00:22:40.880 align:middle line:90%
and get through it.

00:22:40.880 --> 00:22:43.240 align:middle line:84%
But I was a film and
television executive producer.

00:22:43.240 --> 00:22:45.020 align:middle line:84%
And I was quite
happily doing that.

00:22:45.020 --> 00:22:46.830 align:middle line:84%
But then "From
Heartbreak to Happiness"

00:22:46.830 --> 00:22:50.290 align:middle line:84%
was published and endorsed
by my hero, Dr. Wayne Dyer.

00:22:50.290 --> 00:22:52.280 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, OK, that's
my gift to grieving people.

00:22:52.280 --> 00:22:55.100 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go back to
being a film and television

00:22:55.100 --> 00:22:56.030 align:middle line:90%
executive producer.

00:22:56.030 --> 00:22:58.690 align:middle line:84%
But the book brought
grieving people to me.

00:22:58.690 --> 00:23:00.620 align:middle line:84%
And so first, I just, you
know, had coffee with them

00:23:00.620 --> 00:23:01.390 align:middle line:90%
and helped them out.

00:23:01.390 --> 00:23:03.810 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, I got to
the point where, like, hm,

00:23:03.810 --> 00:23:06.790 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have to, uh,
either turn people away or--

00:23:06.790 --> 00:23:08.150 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Take a look at this.

00:23:08.150 --> 00:23:10.330 align:middle line:84%
---or start charging because
this is time consuming.

00:23:10.330 --> 00:23:14.040 align:middle line:84%
And I was stunned to find
that if I-- when I set it up

00:23:14.040 --> 00:23:16.230 align:middle line:84%
as a business and started
charging as a coach, more

00:23:16.230 --> 00:23:17.840 align:middle line:90%
people came to me.

00:23:17.840 --> 00:23:19.960 align:middle line:84%
Because they wanted to know they
could talk to me every week.

00:23:19.960 --> 00:23:22.760 align:middle line:84%
And they-- and they didn't want
to impose on my good nature.

00:23:22.760 --> 00:23:25.140 align:middle line:84%
And then my clients
said, wow, you've

00:23:25.140 --> 00:23:27.480 align:middle line:84%
helped me more in one
session than my therapist

00:23:27.480 --> 00:23:28.640 align:middle line:90%
helped me in two years.

00:23:28.640 --> 00:23:29.620 align:middle line:90%
Can you teach me?

00:23:29.620 --> 00:23:31.510 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, OK, why not?

00:23:31.510 --> 00:23:36.760 align:middle line:10%
So fast forward to today,
we now have a school

00:23:36.760 --> 00:23:41.150 align:middle line:10%
devoted to giving coaches the
skills they need to help people

00:23:41.150 --> 00:23:43.920 align:middle line:10%
release grief, transcend
grief, and become happy

00:23:43.920 --> 00:23:45.840 align:middle line:10%
again much, much more quickly.

00:23:45.840 --> 00:23:48.100 align:middle line:84%
And each coaching session
is 30 minutes or less.

00:23:48.100 --> 00:23:49.760 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: It's such
an incredible story

00:23:49.760 --> 00:23:53.090 align:middle line:84%
that you have of how you
turned a tragedy into something

00:23:53.090 --> 00:23:55.500 align:middle line:84%
that is so purposeful
and so aligned

00:23:55.500 --> 00:23:57.240 align:middle line:90%
with helping other people.

00:23:57.240 --> 00:23:59.480 align:middle line:84%
And just as the
woman that you know

00:23:59.480 --> 00:24:02.530 align:middle line:84%
that had to suffer the loss
of her child to create MADD,

00:24:02.530 --> 00:24:05.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's these different
experiences-- that I look

00:24:05.890 --> 00:24:09.050 align:middle line:84%
at people like you and
go, oh my god, I mean,

00:24:09.050 --> 00:24:10.000 align:middle line:90%
this is your purpose.

00:24:10.000 --> 00:24:11.130 align:middle line:90%
This is your destiny.

00:24:11.130 --> 00:24:12.550 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Well,
it's really a choice.

00:24:12.550 --> 00:24:14.820 align:middle line:84%
I mean, when something
devastating happens,

00:24:14.820 --> 00:24:19.380 align:middle line:84%
you can become bitter or you
can decide to become better.

00:24:19.380 --> 00:24:22.710 align:middle line:84%
And I really feel now--
I truly feel in my heart

00:24:22.710 --> 00:24:25.050 align:middle line:84%
that before I was born--
before I was born,

00:24:25.050 --> 00:24:26.700 align:middle line:90%
God asked for a volunteer.

00:24:26.700 --> 00:24:28.890 align:middle line:84%
And He said, can I
have a volunteer?

00:24:28.890 --> 00:24:30.090 align:middle line:84%
Who'd like to teach
people how to go

00:24:30.090 --> 00:24:31.056 align:middle line:90%
from heartbreak to happiness?

00:24:31.056 --> 00:24:32.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, hey,
pick me-- pick me.

00:24:32.220 --> 00:24:34.220 align:middle line:84%
That sounds like a
cool life mission.

00:24:34.220 --> 00:24:36.290 align:middle line:84%
And then he asked
for a volunteer

00:24:36.290 --> 00:24:39.210 align:middle line:84%
who'd be willing to teach
me what I needed to know.

00:24:39.210 --> 00:24:40.545 align:middle line:90%
And my late husband volunteered.

00:24:40.545 --> 00:24:41.360 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Wow.

00:24:41.360 --> 00:24:45.180 align:middle line:84%
So with that point of view,
there's nothing but gratitude.

00:24:45.180 --> 00:24:47.475 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: You really
can embrace that.

00:24:47.475 --> 00:24:48.800 align:middle line:84%
You really can.
AURORA WINTER: I do.

00:24:48.800 --> 00:24:49.510 align:middle line:90%
You do.

00:24:49.510 --> 00:24:54.400 align:middle line:84%
