00:28:09.240 --> 00:28:10.200 align:middle line:10%
I'm Lisa Garr.

00:28:10.200 --> 00:28:14.900 align:middle line:10%
And my guest is grief coach
Aurora Winter, author of "Grief

00:28:14.900 --> 00:28:16.420 align:middle line:10%
Relief in 30 Minutes."

00:28:16.420 --> 00:28:18.860 align:middle line:84%
And there is a method
that Aurora teaches

00:28:18.860 --> 00:28:20.310 align:middle line:90%
called the Peace Method.

00:28:20.310 --> 00:28:22.730 align:middle line:84%
And this is basically for
anyone who's experiencing

00:28:22.730 --> 00:28:24.040 align:middle line:90%
any type of loss, right?

00:28:24.040 --> 00:28:25.210 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Exactly.
-OK.

00:28:25.210 --> 00:28:27.010 align:middle line:10%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah, I'm so
excited about this process

00:28:27.010 --> 00:28:29.370 align:middle line:10%
because after "From Heartbreak
to Happiness" was published,

00:28:29.370 --> 00:28:31.640 align:middle line:10%
people were like, wow, I
really connect to your story,

00:28:31.640 --> 00:28:34.100 align:middle line:10%
but how can I get through
this more quickly?

00:28:34.100 --> 00:28:36.220 align:middle line:10%
So we have many tools at
the Grief Coach Academy.

00:28:36.220 --> 00:28:37.970 align:middle line:84%
But if I had to
pick just one, it

00:28:37.970 --> 00:28:39.950 align:middle line:84%
would be the Peace
Method-- the fastest

00:28:39.950 --> 00:28:43.310 align:middle line:84%
way to cut through grief
and get to happiness again.

00:28:43.310 --> 00:28:45.690 align:middle line:84%
So the Peace Method
is really easy to use.

00:28:45.690 --> 00:28:47.460 align:middle line:90%
You can-- I'll explain it here.

00:28:47.460 --> 00:28:49.380 align:middle line:84%
And people can do it
as a journaling process

00:28:49.380 --> 00:28:51.170 align:middle line:90%
immediately and do it every day.

00:28:51.170 --> 00:28:52.601 align:middle line:84%
They'll feel much
better very quickly.

00:28:52.601 --> 00:28:53.300 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: OK.

00:28:53.300 --> 00:28:57.900 align:middle line:84%
So it's-- the P stands for
be in the present moment.

00:28:57.900 --> 00:29:01.610 align:middle line:84%
So first, you identify
whatever emotion is going on.

00:29:01.610 --> 00:29:03.720 align:middle line:84%
Every emotion is
linked to a thought.

00:29:03.720 --> 00:29:06.810 align:middle line:84%
So catch like a-- like
a Sherlock Holmes,

00:29:06.810 --> 00:29:10.350 align:middle line:84%
catch the thought that's
linked to that upset feeling.

00:29:10.350 --> 00:29:12.610 align:middle line:84%
And then one thought at
a time, you'll take it

00:29:12.610 --> 00:29:13.890 align:middle line:90%
through the Peace Method.

00:29:13.890 --> 00:29:16.640 align:middle line:84%
So a painful thought
is like a brick.

00:29:16.640 --> 00:29:18.290 align:middle line:90%
So it's imprisoning you.

00:29:18.290 --> 00:29:20.600 align:middle line:84%
You're imprisoned
in a brick prison.

00:29:20.600 --> 00:29:23.990 align:middle line:84%
And if you just try to take the
whole prison wall down at once,

00:29:23.990 --> 00:29:25.860 align:middle line:84%
you're just going to
get a sore shoulder.

00:29:25.860 --> 00:29:30.100 align:middle line:84%
But if you focus on one brick at
a time and work on the mortar,

00:29:30.100 --> 00:29:32.880 align:middle line:84%
you may get it to
loosen or even pop out.

00:29:32.880 --> 00:29:34.861 align:middle line:84%
And then you will focus
on another painful thought

00:29:34.861 --> 00:29:35.560 align:middle line:90%
and another.

00:29:35.560 --> 00:29:37.160 align:middle line:84%
Now, the good news
is-- just like escaping

00:29:37.160 --> 00:29:39.330 align:middle line:84%
a prison-- you don't have
to take down every brick.

00:29:39.330 --> 00:29:41.980 align:middle line:84%
You just need a big enough
hole to escape into the garden

00:29:41.980 --> 00:29:42.720 align:middle line:90%
on the other side.

00:29:42.720 --> 00:29:46.620 align:middle line:84%
So the Peace Method is a really
powerful way of focusing on--

00:29:46.620 --> 00:29:49.000 align:middle line:84%
and we'll give an example
here of one thought at a time.

00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:51.694 align:middle line:84%
So may I explain
what it stands for?

00:29:51.694 --> 00:29:53.260 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Yeah, because
I'm thinking-- I mean,

00:29:53.260 --> 00:29:54.493 align:middle line:84%
that's the first
thing I was thinking

00:29:54.493 --> 00:29:58.490 align:middle line:84%
is that someone's present moment
might be just too painful.

00:29:58.490 --> 00:30:00.380 align:middle line:84%
It's amazing when
you do this-- and I've

00:30:00.380 --> 00:30:01.740 align:middle line:90%
coached many people through it.

00:30:01.740 --> 00:30:04.870 align:middle line:84%
And it usually
takes me 15 minutes.

00:30:04.870 --> 00:30:06.680 align:middle line:90%
So 30 minutes is ample time.

00:30:06.680 --> 00:30:08.630 align:middle line:84%
So what you want to do is
identify the painful thought.

00:30:08.630 --> 00:30:11.980 align:middle line:84%
So in my example, it might be
my husband's death is the worst

00:30:11.980 --> 00:30:13.560 align:middle line:90%
thing that ever happened to me.

00:30:13.560 --> 00:30:16.130 align:middle line:10%
So the P is come into
the present moment.

00:30:16.130 --> 00:30:18.270 align:middle line:10%
The E is express your feelings.

00:30:18.270 --> 00:30:23.290 align:middle line:10%
The A is look to accept or even
can you appreciate something?

00:30:23.290 --> 00:30:25.820 align:middle line:10%
The C is consider the contrary.

00:30:25.820 --> 00:30:28.110 align:middle line:10%
And the E is to find
something that you

00:30:28.110 --> 00:30:31.950 align:middle line:10%
can be enthusiastic
about being or doing.

00:30:31.950 --> 00:30:34.491 align:middle line:10%
So let's use an example
and walk it through.

00:30:34.491 --> 00:30:35.190 align:middle line:10%
LISA GARR: OK.

00:30:35.190 --> 00:30:37.110 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: So
I'm self-coaching--

00:30:37.110 --> 00:30:38.230 align:middle line:90%
imagining I was journaling.

00:30:38.230 --> 00:30:41.000 align:middle line:84%
So I feel upset and I write,
my husband's death is the worst

00:30:41.000 --> 00:30:42.370 align:middle line:90%
thing that ever happened to me.

00:30:42.370 --> 00:30:43.880 align:middle line:90%
So P of the peace method.

00:30:43.880 --> 00:30:51.060 align:middle line:84%
Take a deep breath
and another one.

00:30:51.060 --> 00:30:53.360 align:middle line:84%
And just literally
come into your body--

00:30:53.360 --> 00:30:54.720 align:middle line:90%
come into the present moment.

00:30:54.720 --> 00:30:58.240 align:middle line:84%
And then ask is that painful
thought-- my husband's death is

00:30:58.240 --> 00:30:59.580 align:middle line:84%
the worst thing
that ever happened

00:30:59.580 --> 00:31:05.220 align:middle line:84%
to me-- is that about the past,
the present, or the future?

00:31:05.220 --> 00:31:07.080 align:middle line:90%
Well, it's about the past.

00:31:07.080 --> 00:31:09.340 align:middle line:84%
And we can never
change the past.

00:31:09.340 --> 00:31:12.850 align:middle line:84%
We can only forgive,
make amends, let it go,

00:31:12.850 --> 00:31:13.810 align:middle line:90%
heal, transcend.

00:31:13.810 --> 00:31:15.710 align:middle line:84%
But we can never
change the past.

00:31:15.710 --> 00:31:17.660 align:middle line:84%
And if it had been
about the future,

00:31:17.660 --> 00:31:21.231 align:middle line:84%
we can never solve all
potential future problems.

00:31:21.231 --> 00:31:21.930 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Hm.

00:31:21.930 --> 00:31:25.150 align:middle line:84%
We can-- we can deal with the
one problem slash opportunity

00:31:25.150 --> 00:31:26.690 align:middle line:90%
that's right here-- right now.

00:31:26.690 --> 00:31:30.340 align:middle line:84%
So already that first
step brings clarity.

00:31:30.340 --> 00:31:32.200 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: What if in
that moment of pain,

00:31:32.200 --> 00:31:36.240 align:middle line:84%
you're still-- what is present
is a child who is grieving

00:31:36.240 --> 00:31:38.220 align:middle line:90%
or a bill that's not being paid.

00:31:38.220 --> 00:31:42.530 align:middle line:84%
So that moment is painful
in that very moment.

00:31:42.530 --> 00:31:43.650 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: That's OK.

00:31:43.650 --> 00:31:47.650 align:middle line:84%
Then what you do is you--
rather than pushing away--

00:31:47.650 --> 00:31:48.820 align:middle line:90%
I shouldn't be feeling sad.

00:31:48.820 --> 00:31:50.680 align:middle line:90%
I shouldn't be feeling pain.

00:31:50.680 --> 00:31:55.100 align:middle line:84%
You welcome it and just notice
where it is in your body.

00:31:55.100 --> 00:31:56.490 align:middle line:90%
Notice other painful thoughts.

00:31:56.490 --> 00:31:59.000 align:middle line:84%
But you need to focus
on one brick at a time.

00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:00.260 align:middle line:84%
If you just do a
little bit on all,

00:32:00.260 --> 00:32:01.360 align:middle line:90%
it's not going to go right.

00:32:01.360 --> 00:32:04.970 align:middle line:84%
So if you have an unpaid bill,
what is the painful thought?

00:32:04.970 --> 00:32:07.260 align:middle line:84%
Is the painful thought I
don't have enough time?

00:32:07.260 --> 00:32:09.820 align:middle line:84%
Or is the painful thought
I don't have enough money?

00:32:09.820 --> 00:32:11.510 align:middle line:84%
Or is the painful
thought my husband

00:32:11.510 --> 00:32:13.321 align:middle line:84%
used to take care of the bills?
LISA GARR: Right.

00:32:13.321 --> 00:32:16.850 align:middle line:84%
Or he's not here.
-Don't do 49 at once.

00:32:16.850 --> 00:32:19.280 align:middle line:84%
See which of those
thoughts is the most

00:32:19.280 --> 00:32:22.160 align:middle line:84%
sticky, icky, upsetting--
and then follow that one

00:32:22.160 --> 00:32:23.270 align:middle line:90%
all the way through.

00:32:23.270 --> 00:32:25.100 align:middle line:84%
And then if you want
to do another one,

00:32:25.100 --> 00:32:26.460 align:middle line:84%
follow another one
all the way through.

00:32:26.460 --> 00:32:27.159 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Right.

00:32:27.159 --> 00:32:29.860 align:middle line:84%
So would you like
me to continue giving

00:32:29.860 --> 00:32:31.000 align:middle line:90%
the example around my husband?

00:32:31.000 --> 00:32:33.340 align:middle line:84%
Or did you want to
change it to a bill?

00:32:33.340 --> 00:32:35.440 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: No, no, that's-- I
mean, you answered my question.

00:32:35.440 --> 00:32:36.006 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
AURORA WINTER: All right.

00:32:36.006 --> 00:32:37.610 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Because I'm just--
I'm just imagining this

00:32:37.610 --> 00:32:38.510 align:middle line:90%
as you're going through it.

00:32:38.510 --> 00:32:40.410 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: But the next
step of the Peace Method

00:32:40.410 --> 00:32:42.450 align:middle line:84%
does give you more
opportunity to express

00:32:42.450 --> 00:32:43.420 align:middle line:90%
your thoughts and feelings.

00:32:43.420 --> 00:32:46.040 align:middle line:84%
So using the example
of my husband's death

00:32:46.040 --> 00:32:47.530 align:middle line:84%
is the worst thing that
ever happened to me,

00:32:47.530 --> 00:32:49.180 align:middle line:90%
I came into the present moment.

00:32:49.180 --> 00:32:50.839 align:middle line:84%
It's about the past.
OK.

00:32:50.839 --> 00:32:52.290 align:middle line:84%
The past is not
going to change--

00:32:52.290 --> 00:32:54.230 align:middle line:84%
no matter how much I think it
should have been different.

00:32:54.230 --> 00:32:55.510 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And I'm here
in this present moment.

00:32:55.510 --> 00:32:56.209 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:32:56.209 --> 00:32:59.950 align:middle line:84%
So then E allows you to express
your feelings that come up when

00:32:59.950 --> 00:33:02.187 align:middle line:84%
you think the thought my
husband's death is the worst

00:33:02.187 --> 00:33:03.220 align:middle line:90%
thing that ever happened to me.

00:33:03.220 --> 00:33:05.297 align:middle line:84%
So journal-- vent
all of the thoughts--

00:33:05.297 --> 00:33:06.130 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Talk about it.

00:33:06.130 --> 00:33:06.950 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: All
of the feelings.

00:33:06.950 --> 00:33:07.730 align:middle line:90%
Talk about it.

00:33:07.730 --> 00:33:09.100 align:middle line:90%
Get it off your chest.

00:33:09.100 --> 00:33:12.870 align:middle line:84%
Maybe take two, three,
five minutes on that step.

00:33:12.870 --> 00:33:15.990 align:middle line:84%
And then you'll--
you'll also welcome it.

00:33:15.990 --> 00:33:18.740 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it has some
wisdom for you.

00:33:18.740 --> 00:33:20.250 align:middle line:84%
I think you know,
like, if you had

00:33:20.250 --> 00:33:21.520 align:middle line:84%
a four-year-old--
I know you have

00:33:21.520 --> 00:33:23.349 align:middle line:84%
a daughter who's 10 now, right?
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:33:23.349 --> 00:33:26.040 align:middle line:84%
But when-- imagine when she was
four and she skinned her knee.

00:33:26.040 --> 00:33:27.780 align:middle line:84%
And she'd come in
running, Mommy, Mommy,

00:33:27.780 --> 00:33:28.678 align:middle line:90%
I skinned my knee.

00:33:28.678 --> 00:33:30.370 align:middle line:84%
And to her, it's like
the end of the world.

00:33:30.370 --> 00:33:32.170 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Right
-Would you go stop crying?

00:33:32.170 --> 00:33:34.030 align:middle line:90%
No, you'd say come on my lap.

00:33:34.030 --> 00:33:35.070 align:middle line:90%
Tell me about it.

00:33:35.070 --> 00:33:36.200 align:middle line:84%
What happened?
LISA GARR: Right.

00:33:36.200 --> 00:33:36.899 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:33:36.899 --> 00:33:39.050 align:middle line:84%
So that's the energy we want to
have with our painful thoughts.

00:33:39.050 --> 00:33:40.030 align:middle line:90%
Tell me about it.

00:33:40.030 --> 00:33:40.870 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:33:40.870 --> 00:33:42.790 align:middle line:84%
When we make war
with our thoughts,

00:33:42.790 --> 00:33:44.690 align:middle line:90%
we increase our stress.

00:33:44.690 --> 00:33:46.500 align:middle line:84%
And just like a
four-year-old child,

00:33:46.500 --> 00:33:48.450 align:middle line:84%
their tantrum will increase.
LISA GARR: Ah, yes.

00:33:48.450 --> 00:33:49.250 align:middle line:90%
Because they have some--

00:33:49.250 --> 00:33:51.040 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: It does drive
the thoughts deeper.

00:33:51.040 --> 00:33:52.573 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: They have
something to tell us.

00:33:52.573 --> 00:33:53.897 align:middle line:90%
Just like my nightmares--

00:33:53.897 --> 00:33:55.130 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Are
telling you something.

00:33:55.130 --> 00:33:56.730 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Every
night, you know, seeing him

00:33:56.730 --> 00:33:57.920 align:middle line:90%
die again and again and again.

00:33:57.920 --> 00:33:59.330 align:middle line:90%
I did not enjoy that.

00:33:59.330 --> 00:34:03.160 align:middle line:84%
But it had some gift hidden
in that-- to call me to wake

00:34:03.160 --> 00:34:04.220 align:middle line:90%
up to the present moment.

00:34:04.220 --> 00:34:08.260 align:middle line:84%
So our painful thoughts have
a gift for us if we can--

00:34:08.260 --> 00:34:10.070 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: A beautiful
way of looking at it.

00:34:10.070 --> 00:34:10.350 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: --find it.

00:34:10.350 --> 00:34:11.916 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Yes, if you
can find the gift in it.

00:34:11.916 --> 00:34:12.735 align:middle line:90%
But they're there.

00:34:12.735 --> 00:34:14.350 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: They are there.

00:34:14.350 --> 00:34:18.989 align:middle line:84%
And then A for the Peace Method
stands for can you accept it?

00:34:18.989 --> 00:34:20.770 align:middle line:84%
So my husband's
death is the worst

00:34:20.770 --> 00:34:21.840 align:middle line:90%
thing that ever happened to me.

00:34:21.840 --> 00:34:24.900 align:middle line:84%
The acceptance would sound
like, well, that could be so.

00:34:24.900 --> 00:34:25.600 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:34:25.600 --> 00:34:27.820 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it is the worst thing
that ever happened to me.

00:34:27.820 --> 00:34:28.880 align:middle line:90%
I can allow that.

00:34:28.880 --> 00:34:31.150 align:middle line:90%
I can accept that as true.

00:34:31.150 --> 00:34:33.885 align:middle line:84%
I don't have to make
war with that idea.

00:34:33.885 --> 00:34:36.520 align:middle line:84%
So-- and even just
that is more peaceful.

00:34:36.520 --> 00:34:39.909 align:middle line:84%
When we make war with ideas,
it increases our stress.

00:34:39.909 --> 00:34:43.401 align:middle line:84%
It-- it prematurely ages
ourselves by up to a decade.

00:34:43.401 --> 00:34:44.300 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Wow.
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:34:44.300 --> 00:34:44.469 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:34:44.469 --> 00:34:45.769 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Yeah, I
can understand that.

00:34:45.769 --> 00:34:47.300 align:middle line:90%
That adds aging to grief.

00:34:47.300 --> 00:34:49.750 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: As you go through
this process, again and again,

00:34:49.750 --> 00:34:53.940 align:middle line:84%
different times of the day or
if it's different days, do you

00:34:53.940 --> 00:34:55.940 align:middle line:84%
notice that it gets
easier and easier?

00:34:55.940 --> 00:34:57.740 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to continue
to go through the process.

00:34:57.740 --> 00:34:59.320 align:middle line:84%
But does--
AURORA WINTER: It gets easier.

00:34:59.320 --> 00:35:01.250 align:middle line:90%
It gets faster.

00:35:01.250 --> 00:35:06.140 align:middle line:84%
You become friendly with your
own wisdom-- your own guidance.

00:35:06.140 --> 00:35:09.330 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Why do we want to
speed up grieving so much?

00:35:09.330 --> 00:35:10.860 align:middle line:90%
I'm sure you've been asked this.

00:35:10.860 --> 00:35:12.890 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Well, who--
I want to speed it up, too.

00:35:12.890 --> 00:35:17.080 align:middle line:84%
I'm all about let's get to
the nut of this quickly.

00:35:17.080 --> 00:35:20.370 align:middle line:84%
Because you know, people suffer
five to eight years typically.

00:35:20.370 --> 00:35:22.640 align:middle line:84%
And it's not their fault
they don't know what to do.

00:35:22.640 --> 00:35:26.710 align:middle line:84%
But my experiences with
the Peace Method, people

00:35:26.710 --> 00:35:30.510 align:middle line:84%
can get through it sometimes
in one 30-minute session.

00:35:30.510 --> 00:35:34.990 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes in a month doing it
on their own-- 30 minutes a day.

00:35:34.990 --> 00:35:37.040 align:middle line:84%
But you can get through
it much more quickly.

00:35:37.040 --> 00:35:39.600 align:middle line:84%
But it's-- there's
two kinds of pain.

00:35:39.600 --> 00:35:41.660 align:middle line:90%
One is sort of the clean pain.

00:35:41.660 --> 00:35:44.490 align:middle line:84%
My husband died--
clean the pain.

00:35:44.490 --> 00:35:45.410 align:middle line:90%
It's like agony.

00:35:45.410 --> 00:35:46.210 align:middle line:90%
I loved him.

00:35:46.210 --> 00:35:47.080 align:middle line:90%
He's dead.

00:35:47.080 --> 00:35:51.770 align:middle line:84%
But the dirty pain is all
the thoughts that I project.

00:35:51.770 --> 00:35:52.480 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Ah.

00:35:52.480 --> 00:35:54.700 align:middle line:90%
It was my fault is dirty pain.

00:35:54.700 --> 00:35:57.290 align:middle line:84%
I'll always be
alone is dirty pain.

00:35:57.290 --> 00:36:00.270 align:middle line:90%
My son won't be OK-- dirty pain.

00:36:00.270 --> 00:36:01.060 align:middle line:90%
That's not true.

00:36:01.060 --> 00:36:01.760 align:middle line:90%
We don't even know.

00:36:01.760 --> 00:36:05.750 align:middle line:84%
Those are all-- so
it's-- like tears

00:36:05.750 --> 00:36:07.470 align:middle line:90%
are a shower for the soul.

00:36:07.470 --> 00:36:11.050 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to erase
grief in my point of view.

00:36:11.050 --> 00:36:14.670 align:middle line:84%
Because I think the clean
part of grief is just-- it's

00:36:14.670 --> 00:36:16.510 align:middle line:84%
the front of the hand--
the back of the hand--

00:36:16.510 --> 00:36:19.090 align:middle line:90%
grief, love, grief, love.

00:36:19.090 --> 00:36:22.050 align:middle line:84%
If you are a person with a
whole heart, you will love

00:36:22.050 --> 00:36:23.610 align:middle line:84%
and you will grieve.
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:36:23.610 --> 00:36:25.990 align:middle line:84%
But we don't want to have the
dirty pain with the getting

00:36:25.990 --> 00:36:29.040 align:middle line:84%
stuck in the well of
grief-- with being

00:36:29.040 --> 00:36:30.590 align:middle line:90%
paralyzed and immobilized.

00:36:30.590 --> 00:36:32.821 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And projecting all
of your thoughts around it.

00:36:32.821 --> 00:36:34.720 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah, and not
being able to get out of bed

00:36:34.720 --> 00:36:36.510 align:middle line:90%
or not being able to love again.

00:36:36.510 --> 00:36:38.930 align:middle line:84%
So we want to let
go of those parts.

00:36:38.930 --> 00:36:40.582 align:middle line:90%
And then it can even be sweet.

00:36:40.582 --> 00:36:43.620 align:middle line:84%
You know, like, when my son gets
married, I will have a moment.

00:36:43.620 --> 00:36:45.070 align:middle line:84%
I might even cry.
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:36:45.070 --> 00:36:47.440 align:middle line:84%
Oh, gosh, I wish
my husband was here.

00:36:47.440 --> 00:36:49.740 align:middle line:90%
But it will be tears of love.

00:36:49.740 --> 00:36:51.220 align:middle line:90%
It will be a beautiful thing.

00:36:51.220 --> 00:36:53.300 align:middle line:90%
It won't be tears of anger.

00:36:53.300 --> 00:36:54.745 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: The tears
that debilitate you.

00:36:54.745 --> 00:36:55.310 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: No.
-Yes.

00:36:55.310 --> 00:36:56.730 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: It'll
be a celebration

00:36:56.730 --> 00:36:59.750 align:middle line:84%
that I still love him and
would have loved to have him

00:36:59.750 --> 00:37:01.030 align:middle line:90%
be at my son's wedding.

00:37:01.030 --> 00:37:02.540 align:middle line:84%
That's a lot of
verbs to conjugate.

00:37:02.540 --> 00:37:03.240 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Right.

00:37:03.240 --> 00:37:05.310 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Anyway, so go
back to the Peace Methods?

00:37:05.310 --> 00:37:06.140 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes, yes.

00:37:06.140 --> 00:37:08.610 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: OK,
so you can do-- the A

00:37:08.610 --> 00:37:11.370 align:middle line:84%
can either just be to
allow or accept what

00:37:11.370 --> 00:37:13.090 align:middle line:90%
is without making a war on it.

00:37:13.090 --> 00:37:15.370 align:middle line:84%
Or you can even look,
is there something

00:37:15.370 --> 00:37:17.830 align:middle line:84%
you can appreciate-- just like
the front of the hand, back

00:37:17.830 --> 00:37:18.900 align:middle line:90%
of the hand.

00:37:18.900 --> 00:37:21.390 align:middle line:84%
So I could appreciate my
husband's death as the worst

00:37:21.390 --> 00:37:22.570 align:middle line:90%
thing that ever happened to me.

00:37:22.570 --> 00:37:26.290 align:middle line:84%
I would only feel that way
if we had had a great love.

00:37:26.290 --> 00:37:28.340 align:middle line:84%
So I can appreciate
the time we shared.

00:37:28.340 --> 00:37:29.850 align:middle line:90%
I can appreciate the love.

00:37:29.850 --> 00:37:31.605 align:middle line:90%
I can appreciate our son.

00:37:31.605 --> 00:37:34.422 align:middle line:84%
I already start to feel
better, right-- appreciation.

00:37:34.422 --> 00:37:36.470 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:37:36.470 --> 00:37:37.950 align:middle line:84%
Then, the next step
of the Peace Method

00:37:37.950 --> 00:37:40.650 align:middle line:90%
is to consider the contrary.

00:37:40.650 --> 00:37:42.690 align:middle line:84%
So considering the
contrary, what's

00:37:42.690 --> 00:37:45.000 align:middle line:84%
the opposite to
my husband's death

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:47.970 align:middle line:84%
was the worst thing that
ever happened to me?

00:37:47.970 --> 00:37:51.590 align:middle line:84%
The most obvious it was the best
thing that ever happened to me.

00:37:51.590 --> 00:37:52.570 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: That's a big step.

00:37:52.570 --> 00:37:55.750 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: That's a big
step but just try it on.

00:37:55.750 --> 00:37:57.210 align:middle line:90%
And it's like going shopping.

00:37:57.210 --> 00:37:59.580 align:middle line:84%
Like if you and I go shopping
together, and I say, Lisa,

00:37:59.580 --> 00:38:01.570 align:middle line:84%
you would look awesome
in that red dress.

00:38:01.570 --> 00:38:02.925 align:middle line:84%
You might say red
is not my color.

00:38:02.925 --> 00:38:04.650 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, just try it on.

00:38:04.650 --> 00:38:05.960 align:middle line:90%
You don't have to buy it.

00:38:05.960 --> 00:38:07.469 align:middle line:84%
So you try--
LISA GARR: OK.

00:38:07.469 --> 00:38:10.760 align:middle line:84%
You try it on-- just
like you do at the store.

00:38:10.760 --> 00:38:13.500 align:middle line:84%
And you can go, holy moly,
you were right, Aurora.

00:38:13.500 --> 00:38:14.940 align:middle line:90%
This dress-- I look awesome.

00:38:14.940 --> 00:38:15.830 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to buy it.

00:38:15.830 --> 00:38:17.330 align:middle line:90%
Or you can go, I tried it on.

00:38:17.330 --> 00:38:18.804 align:middle line:84%
It's not me.
All right.

00:38:18.804 --> 00:38:22.051 align:middle line:84%
So in the same way, just
try it on playfully.

00:38:22.051 --> 00:38:23.710 align:middle line:84%
And--
LISA GARR: Try on the phrase.

00:38:23.710 --> 00:38:26.917 align:middle line:84%
Try on the idea of acceptance
of that that's the best

00:38:26.917 --> 00:38:27.950 align:middle line:90%
thing that could have happened.

00:38:27.950 --> 00:38:29.416 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: The whole
thing-- just try it

00:38:29.416 --> 00:38:32.050 align:middle line:90%
on to discover your own wisdom.

00:38:32.050 --> 00:38:33.900 align:middle line:84%
So when I try on
my husband's death

00:38:33.900 --> 00:38:36.430 align:middle line:84%
was the best thing that
ever happened to me,

00:38:36.430 --> 00:38:38.772 align:middle line:90%
I find deep truth in that.

00:38:38.772 --> 00:38:40.680 align:middle line:90%
In some ways, it was.

00:38:40.680 --> 00:38:44.620 align:middle line:84%
Through his death, he became
my greatest spiritual teacher.

00:38:44.620 --> 00:38:47.860 align:middle line:84%
Through his death, I got clear
on what really matters in life.

00:38:47.860 --> 00:38:49.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's not making
a lot of money.

00:38:49.940 --> 00:38:51.570 align:middle line:90%
It's not having the big house.

00:38:51.570 --> 00:38:52.450 align:middle line:90%
It's people.

00:38:52.450 --> 00:38:53.320 align:middle line:90%
It's love.

00:38:53.320 --> 00:38:54.320 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes, relationships.

00:38:54.320 --> 00:38:55.350 align:middle line:90%
It's being of service.

00:38:55.350 --> 00:38:57.140 align:middle line:90%
It's making a difference.

00:38:57.140 --> 00:39:00.800 align:middle line:84%
And through his death, you
know, fast forward now 20 years,

00:39:00.800 --> 00:39:02.910 align:middle line:84%
I'm now a catalyst
for other people

00:39:02.910 --> 00:39:06.430 align:middle line:84%
to get through their loss, to
shine their light brightly,

00:39:06.430 --> 00:39:08.030 align:middle line:84%
and to make a
difference in the world.

00:39:08.030 --> 00:39:12.510 align:middle line:84%
So I can really take that on
and say, yeah, that's true.

00:39:12.510 --> 00:39:15.550 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: But how long do
you think it should take

00:39:15.550 --> 00:39:17.347 align:middle line:84%
someone to get to that place?
[LAUGHTER]

00:39:17.347 --> 00:39:19.180 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: I mean, you went
through this great process.

00:39:19.180 --> 00:39:21.180 align:middle line:84%
And now you're helping
other people with it.

00:39:21.180 --> 00:39:22.760 align:middle line:84%
And that's a-- that's a
wonderful thing to do.

00:39:22.760 --> 00:39:27.900 align:middle line:84%
But when you coach people, do
say five years-- five months--

00:39:27.900 --> 00:39:30.520 align:middle line:90%
or is it different for everyone?

00:39:30.520 --> 00:39:32.080 align:middle line:84%
Well, the honest answer
to that is I think

00:39:32.080 --> 00:39:36.310 align:middle line:84%
should is about the most violent
word in the English language.

00:39:36.310 --> 00:39:38.500 align:middle line:84%
And I catch myself
even to replace

00:39:38.500 --> 00:39:42.630 align:middle line:90%
should with could or would.

00:39:42.630 --> 00:39:45.590 align:middle line:84%
I think it's very
much a limiting belief

00:39:45.590 --> 00:39:48.360 align:middle line:84%
that it's to honor
the person who

00:39:48.360 --> 00:39:53.240 align:middle line:84%
died to stay mired in grief.
LISA GARR: Wow.

00:39:53.240 --> 00:39:58.860 align:middle line:84%
It's like how long should it
take for a broken arm to heal?

00:39:58.860 --> 00:40:04.150 align:middle line:84%
Months, weeks, maybe,
you know, not five years.

00:40:04.150 --> 00:40:05.410 align:middle line:90%
So but--

00:40:05.410 --> 00:40:06.621 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Not days, either.
-Yeah.

00:40:06.621 --> 00:40:07.320 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Right?

00:40:07.320 --> 00:40:09.090 align:middle line:84%
But-- but you do
you take action.

00:40:09.090 --> 00:40:10.090 align:middle line:90%
You go to the doctor.

00:40:10.090 --> 00:40:11.200 align:middle line:90%
You put on the cast.

00:40:11.200 --> 00:40:12.120 align:middle line:90%
You da da da da da.

00:40:12.120 --> 00:40:13.290 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Right.

00:40:13.290 --> 00:40:14.680 align:middle line:90%
People get stuck in grief.

00:40:14.680 --> 00:40:17.410 align:middle line:84%
And partly, I think it's--
you know, grief, I think,

00:40:17.410 --> 00:40:20.280 align:middle line:84%
is like you're walking along the
park on a beautiful sunny day.

00:40:20.280 --> 00:40:23.041 align:middle line:84%
You don't notice, and
you walk into a hole.

00:40:23.041 --> 00:40:23.740 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:40:23.740 --> 00:40:27.850 align:middle line:84%
And you can stay stuck in
the bottom of that dark hole

00:40:27.850 --> 00:40:31.600 align:middle line:84%
forever, but with-- but
with a step-by-step recipe--

00:40:31.600 --> 00:40:33.060 align:middle line:84%
if somebody comes
along or if you

00:40:33.060 --> 00:40:36.010 align:middle line:84%
use the Peace Method at
home alone, you can go,

00:40:36.010 --> 00:40:37.240 align:middle line:90%
hey, I'm not alone.

00:40:37.240 --> 00:40:40.460 align:middle line:84%
Here's a road map, and
step-by-step I can walk up.

00:40:40.460 --> 00:40:41.660 align:middle line:84%
If you have a grief
coach, you know,

00:40:41.660 --> 00:40:43.810 align:middle line:84%
they'll shine a flashlight down
there-- say you're not alone.

00:40:43.810 --> 00:40:44.510 align:middle line:90%
I'm here.

00:40:44.510 --> 00:40:46.610 align:middle line:84%
A friend can say
you're not alone.

00:40:46.610 --> 00:40:47.594 align:middle line:90%
I'm here and have patience.

00:40:47.594 --> 00:40:49.560 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Well, and there's
a lot of cultural beliefs also

00:40:49.560 --> 00:40:51.390 align:middle line:84%
that go along with
honoring the dead

00:40:51.390 --> 00:40:53.050 align:middle line:90%
and taking the time to grieve.

00:40:53.050 --> 00:40:54.440 align:middle line:90%
And it can be decades.

00:40:54.440 --> 00:40:55.690 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there are
certain cultures--

00:40:55.690 --> 00:40:58.530 align:middle line:84%
and I'm sure you've
heard from in the process

00:40:58.530 --> 00:41:00.670 align:middle line:90%
of you bringing out your work.

00:41:00.670 --> 00:41:04.540 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Well, I say
honor your relationship

00:41:04.540 --> 00:41:07.300 align:middle line:84%
with the person who died
by making their death be

00:41:07.300 --> 00:41:10.560 align:middle line:90%
meaningful not meaningless.

00:41:10.560 --> 00:41:13.660 align:middle line:84%
And how you can best make it
meaningful is transcend it

00:41:13.660 --> 00:41:17.990 align:middle line:84%
yourself and then do something--
whether it's just to be

00:41:17.990 --> 00:41:20.700 align:middle line:84%
a better mother to your own
children because you can get

00:41:20.700 --> 00:41:23.680 align:middle line:84%
out of bed-- or whether it's
Mothers Against Drunk Driving

00:41:23.680 --> 00:41:25.840 align:middle line:84%
or whether it's starting the
Grief Coach Academy or becoming

00:41:25.840 --> 00:41:28.460 align:middle line:84%
a grief coach or like what
you're doing, Lisa, spreading

00:41:28.460 --> 00:41:29.480 align:middle line:90%
the word-- helping people--

00:41:29.480 --> 00:41:30.720 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Right, right.

00:41:30.720 --> 00:41:36.040 align:middle line:84%
Find a way to honor your love
by doing something of meaning.

00:41:36.040 --> 00:41:36.975 align:middle line:90%
That's my challenge.

00:41:36.975 --> 00:41:39.560 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: That makes
a huge amount of sense.

00:41:39.560 --> 00:41:40.260 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:41:40.260 --> 00:41:41.430 align:middle line:90%
It gets you unstuck, too.

00:41:41.430 --> 00:41:43.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can be a sponsor
to someone who is grieving.

00:41:43.920 --> 00:41:47.000 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just like an AA sponsor
is someone who's recovering,

00:41:47.000 --> 00:41:48.750 align:middle line:84%
you could-- you
could do anything,

00:41:48.750 --> 00:41:50.750 align:middle line:90%
even if it's in a small way.

00:41:50.750 --> 00:41:55.480 align:middle line:84%
You could spend those moments
of grieving to go and spend

00:41:55.480 --> 00:41:58.450 align:middle line:84%
more time with your children or
something and do something fun.

00:41:58.450 --> 00:41:59.310 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:41:59.310 --> 00:42:00.030 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:42:00.030 --> 00:42:02.610 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking of my
friend, and I-- I-- I mean,

00:42:02.610 --> 00:42:04.550 align:middle line:84%
there's so many things that
you're talking about that

00:42:04.550 --> 00:42:05.551 align:middle line:90%
could so much help her.

00:42:05.551 --> 00:42:07.450 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Well, I think
Mother Teresa said it right.

00:42:07.450 --> 00:42:09.010 align:middle line:90%
We can do no great things.

00:42:09.010 --> 00:42:11.200 align:middle line:84%
We can only do small
things with great love.

00:42:11.200 --> 00:42:12.180 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: That's very true.

00:42:12.180 --> 00:42:14.150 align:middle line:84%
And so it-- it is
not a small thing

00:42:14.150 --> 00:42:16.310 align:middle line:84%
to call somebody who's
heartbroken and say, hey,

00:42:16.310 --> 00:42:17.010 align:middle line:90%
I'm here.

00:42:17.010 --> 00:42:17.760 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:42:17.760 --> 00:42:18.870 align:middle line:90%
I'll listen.

00:42:18.870 --> 00:42:21.350 align:middle line:84%
It's not a small thing to say,
hey, I'm not a grief coach,

00:42:21.350 --> 00:42:23.300 align:middle line:90%
but I'll pay for you to get one.

00:42:23.300 --> 00:42:26.450 align:middle line:84%
It's not a small thing to just
say, I don't know what to say.

00:42:26.450 --> 00:42:28.420 align:middle line:84%
But I could come on over
and babysit the kids

00:42:28.420 --> 00:42:29.750 align:middle line:90%
if you'd like to go to the gym.

00:42:29.750 --> 00:42:30.530 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:42:30.530 --> 00:42:32.640 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's talk a little
bit about what to say

00:42:32.640 --> 00:42:34.950 align:middle line:84%
and what not to say to
someone who is grieving.

00:42:34.950 --> 00:42:36.690 align:middle line:84%
Because you've really
written the handbook on this.

00:42:36.690 --> 00:42:37.460 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:42:37.460 --> 00:42:40.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it-- it's
saying things that people

00:42:40.030 --> 00:42:43.000 align:middle line:84%
say just because we've
always heard them.

00:42:43.000 --> 00:42:45.054 align:middle line:84%
But they are more harmful
than they are good.

00:42:45.054 --> 00:42:45.920 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Absolutely.

00:42:45.920 --> 00:42:47.310 align:middle line:84%
Let me come to that
in just a second.

00:42:47.310 --> 00:42:48.830 align:middle line:84%
And let me just finish
the Peace Method.

00:42:48.830 --> 00:42:49.529 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: OK.

00:42:49.529 --> 00:42:52.560 align:middle line:84%
The last step is the E of the
Peace Method is for enthusiasm.

00:42:52.560 --> 00:42:55.620 align:middle line:84%
So what do you
consciously choose?

00:42:55.620 --> 00:42:57.350 align:middle line:90%
And so that could be an action.

00:42:57.350 --> 00:42:58.720 align:middle line:84%
It could be helping
somebody else.

00:42:58.720 --> 00:43:01.100 align:middle line:90%
It could be going to the gym.

00:43:01.100 --> 00:43:02.010 align:middle line:90%
It could be eating better.

00:43:02.010 --> 00:43:04.880 align:middle line:84%
It could be, like, I consciously
choose that-- you know,

00:43:04.880 --> 00:43:07.940 align:middle line:84%
to help other people get
through grief more quickly.

00:43:07.940 --> 00:43:10.770 align:middle line:84%
First, I chose to share my story
"From Heartbreak to Happiness"

00:43:10.770 --> 00:43:13.200 align:middle line:84%
to help other people
know they're not alone--

00:43:13.200 --> 00:43:14.720 align:middle line:90%
that grieving is a process.

00:43:14.720 --> 00:43:17.060 align:middle line:84%
Now, as the founder of
the Grief Coach Academy,

00:43:17.060 --> 00:43:18.850 align:middle line:84%
give them a tool--
the Peace Method,

00:43:18.850 --> 00:43:20.740 align:middle line:84%
which they can work through
their grief in 30 minutes.

00:43:20.740 --> 00:43:23.460 align:middle line:84%
But what is it for you
on your painful thought?

00:43:23.460 --> 00:43:26.960 align:middle line:84%
So don't just leave it with
exploring your feelings.

00:43:26.960 --> 00:43:29.710 align:middle line:84%
Make a decision and take
some action-- no matter

00:43:29.710 --> 00:43:32.890 align:middle line:84%
how small-- even if it's
only to write one email

00:43:32.890 --> 00:43:35.170 align:middle line:84%
or spend five minutes
checking out something

00:43:35.170 --> 00:43:38.310 align:middle line:84%
or go out for a walk or spend
five minutes in the sunshine.

00:43:38.310 --> 00:43:41.169 align:middle line:84%
Take some action no matter
how small at the end

00:43:41.169 --> 00:43:42.035 align:middle line:90%
of doing the Peace Method.

00:43:42.035 --> 00:43:43.580 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: That gives
you a little bit of joy.

00:43:43.580 --> 00:43:44.180 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: A
little bit of joy.

00:43:44.180 --> 00:43:46.341 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Back and then those
little moments of joy stack up.

00:43:46.341 --> 00:43:47.040 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Eh.

00:43:47.040 --> 00:43:47.940 align:middle line:84%
That's what you
mean by enthusiasm?

00:43:47.940 --> 00:43:48.939 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: They really do.

00:43:48.939 --> 00:43:50.350 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, that's what I
mean by enthusiasm.

00:43:50.350 --> 00:43:52.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, I chose the
word enthusiasm

00:43:52.430 --> 00:43:55.611 align:middle line:84%
because it means, like, "en
theo," to be filled with God.

00:43:55.611 --> 00:43:56.310 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Hm.

00:43:56.310 --> 00:43:57.730 align:middle line:84%
So what do you
choose to be filled

00:43:57.730 --> 00:44:01.490 align:middle line:84%
with God or spirit about?
LISA GARR: Very good.

00:44:01.490 --> 00:44:04.380 align:middle line:84%
So it could be that,
as you said, exercise.

00:44:04.380 --> 00:44:05.590 align:middle line:90%
It can be sunlight.

00:44:05.590 --> 00:44:06.910 align:middle line:90%
It could be a connection.

00:44:06.910 --> 00:44:09.600 align:middle line:84%
It could be anything--
looking at the veins

00:44:09.600 --> 00:44:11.150 align:middle line:84%
in leaves-- whatever
gives you just

00:44:11.150 --> 00:44:12.290 align:middle line:90%
a moment of connection and joy.

00:44:12.290 --> 00:44:14.123 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: A little bit
of joy-- fresh raspberries.

00:44:14.123 --> 00:44:15.360 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Fresh
raspberries-- good.

00:44:15.360 --> 00:44:16.310 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Exactly.
LISA GARR: Good for you.

00:44:16.310 --> 00:44:17.009 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:44:17.009 --> 00:44:18.180 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: So
that's a great way--

00:44:18.180 --> 00:44:19.860 align:middle line:84%
that's a great thing
to say, though--

00:44:19.860 --> 00:44:21.600 align:middle line:84%
the chips in a
chocolate chip cookie--

00:44:21.600 --> 00:44:22.774 align:middle line:90%
little things like that--

00:44:22.774 --> 00:44:23.740 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Little things.

00:44:23.740 --> 00:44:24.750 align:middle line:90%
---is really what it means.

00:44:24.750 --> 00:44:26.550 align:middle line:10%
AURORA WINTER: And helping
other people is the fastest

00:44:26.550 --> 00:44:27.610 align:middle line:10%
way to get out of yourself.

00:44:27.610 --> 00:44:30.780 align:middle line:10%
So if you're feeling really low,
paradoxically getting out there

00:44:30.780 --> 00:44:32.810 align:middle line:10%
and helping somebody
who is dealing with even

00:44:32.810 --> 00:44:34.300 align:middle line:10%
more challenges can be great.

00:44:34.300 --> 00:44:36.450 align:middle line:10%
So the Peace Method,
just those five steps:

00:44:36.450 --> 00:44:39.440 align:middle line:10%
come into the present moment,
express your feelings,

00:44:39.440 --> 00:44:42.920 align:middle line:10%
accept or appreciate,
consider the contrary,

00:44:42.920 --> 00:44:45.510 align:middle line:10%
and end with enthusiasm.
LISA GARR: OK.

00:44:45.510 --> 00:44:47.470 align:middle line:84%
And then now, do
you-- the Grief Wheel,

00:44:47.470 --> 00:44:49.500 align:middle line:84%
is that a part of
the Peace process?

00:44:49.500 --> 00:44:51.010 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: The
Grief Wheel is actually

00:44:51.010 --> 00:44:53.190 align:middle line:84%
a different coaching
process that we teach

00:44:53.190 --> 00:44:54.300 align:middle line:90%
at the Grief Coach Academy.

00:44:54.300 --> 00:44:58.280 align:middle line:10%
So I teach over a dozen
different coaching processes

00:44:58.280 --> 00:45:00.690 align:middle line:10%
that take about 30
minutes each to give

00:45:00.690 --> 00:45:02.180 align:middle line:10%
people a step-by-step recipe.

00:45:02.180 --> 00:45:04.790 align:middle line:10%
And they can get some videos
with some free coach training

00:45:04.790 --> 00:45:06.464 align:middle line:10%
online, as well, at
griefcoachacademy.com.

00:45:06.464 --> 00:45:07.330 align:middle line:10%
LISA GARR: Which is great.

00:45:07.330 --> 00:45:08.704 align:middle line:84%
And then you also
train coaches, right?

00:45:08.704 --> 00:45:09.870 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: And
I train coaches.

00:45:09.870 --> 00:45:12.390 align:middle line:84%
Which is a terrific way for
people to be able to continue

00:45:12.390 --> 00:45:14.104 align:middle line:84%
on and to help, as well.
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:45:14.104 --> 00:45:15.570 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And I like
the fact that you have

00:45:15.570 --> 00:45:18.550 align:middle line:84%
several different tools because
it's not just one tool that's

00:45:18.550 --> 00:45:19.564 align:middle line:90%
going to work for everyone.

00:45:19.564 --> 00:45:20.330 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Exactly.

00:45:20.330 --> 00:45:22.970 align:middle line:84%
And there's many different
levels of the processes where

00:45:22.970 --> 00:45:24.920 align:middle line:90%
you go in and out, up and down.

00:45:24.920 --> 00:45:26.670 align:middle line:84%
So going through
the different tools

00:45:26.670 --> 00:45:29.020 align:middle line:84%
is just a way of staying
in action about something.

00:45:29.020 --> 00:45:31.050 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Staying in
action is so important.

00:45:31.050 --> 00:45:33.540 align:middle line:84%
And what I like about the
Peace Method is kind of like

00:45:33.540 --> 00:45:37.210 align:middle line:84%
if people want to get
fit, what would be

00:45:37.210 --> 00:45:38.940 align:middle line:90%
one class that you'd recommend?

00:45:38.940 --> 00:45:40.910 align:middle line:84%
So the Peace Method is
kind of the equivalent of

00:45:40.910 --> 00:45:42.960 align:middle line:90%
your favorite power yoga class.

00:45:42.960 --> 00:45:44.580 align:middle line:84%
It hits five different
muscle groups.

00:45:44.580 --> 00:45:45.279 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:45:45.279 --> 00:45:46.930 align:middle line:84%
---so to speak, but
that doesn't mean that

00:45:46.930 --> 00:45:49.640 align:middle line:84%
it's not important to also
eat right and meditate

00:45:49.640 --> 00:45:50.480 align:middle line:90%
and do other things.

00:45:50.480 --> 00:45:53.200 align:middle line:84%
So we have other processes
at the Grief Coach Academy.

00:45:53.200 --> 00:45:54.880 align:middle line:84%
Did you want me to talk
about what to say--

00:45:54.880 --> 00:45:55.920 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Yes.
-And what not to say?

00:45:55.920 --> 00:45:57.350 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Very,
very helpful, yes.

00:45:57.350 --> 00:46:00.460 align:middle line:84%
What-- what would you say to
someone that would be-- well,

00:46:00.460 --> 00:46:01.571 align:middle line:84%
let's start with
what not to say.

00:46:01.571 --> 00:46:02.270 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: OK.

00:46:02.270 --> 00:46:03.760 align:middle line:84%
Because that is the
most common stuff.

00:46:03.760 --> 00:46:03.855 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Basically--

00:46:03.855 --> 00:46:05.420 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: I've said
this before to people.

00:46:05.420 --> 00:46:06.340 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:46:06.340 --> 00:46:08.239 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Basically if
it's coming out of your mouth

00:46:08.239 --> 00:46:11.096 align:middle line:84%
automatically and everybody else
says it, probably not helpful.

00:46:11.096 --> 00:46:12.040 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Such as--

00:46:12.040 --> 00:46:14.774 align:middle line:84%
Such as I'm sorry--
not so helpful.

00:46:14.774 --> 00:46:15.640 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Not so helpful.

00:46:15.640 --> 00:46:16.880 align:middle line:90%
You know why?

00:46:16.880 --> 00:46:18.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'll tell you
why in a second.

00:46:18.490 --> 00:46:19.420 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:46:19.420 --> 00:46:20.700 align:middle line:90%
It was just God's will.

00:46:20.700 --> 00:46:22.890 align:middle line:90%
Be grateful you had him so long.

00:46:22.890 --> 00:46:24.150 align:middle line:90%
Um, I--

00:46:24.150 --> 00:46:25.910 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: You'll
find another husband.

00:46:25.910 --> 00:46:27.190 align:middle line:90%
You'll find it or you're young.

00:46:27.190 --> 00:46:28.690 align:middle line:90%
You can have another child.

00:46:28.690 --> 00:46:30.114 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Yes.
Ooh, yeah.

00:46:30.114 --> 00:46:31.710 align:middle line:84%
All of these things
are not so helpful.

00:46:31.710 --> 00:46:35.950 align:middle line:84%
Basically anything that tries
to minimize the person's

00:46:35.950 --> 00:46:40.550 align:middle line:84%
authentic experience with
some automatic shield comment

00:46:40.550 --> 00:46:42.010 align:middle line:90%
is not helpful.

00:46:42.010 --> 00:46:45.600 align:middle line:84%
The reason why I'm sorry
is kind of a 50-50 one--

00:46:45.600 --> 00:46:49.610 align:middle line:84%
if people who knew my husband
said I'm sorry, that was

00:46:49.610 --> 00:46:51.710 align:middle line:90%
fine because they were sorry.

00:46:51.710 --> 00:46:53.480 align:middle line:84%
They knew him.
LISA GARR: OK.

00:46:53.480 --> 00:46:57.120 align:middle line:84%
But if somebody who never
knew him-- didn't know me

00:46:57.120 --> 00:46:59.230 align:middle line:84%
and, you know, asked me
out on a date and said,

00:46:59.230 --> 00:47:00.750 align:middle line:84%
you know, how long
have you been divorced?

00:47:00.750 --> 00:47:02.160 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say, well,
actually, I'm a widow.

00:47:02.160 --> 00:47:05.900 align:middle line:84%
And they're like I'm
sorry, it's disconnecting

00:47:05.900 --> 00:47:09.360 align:middle line:84%
because it projects this
whole story about me.

00:47:09.360 --> 00:47:10.767 align:middle line:84%
And they don't
even know who I am.

00:47:10.767 --> 00:47:11.800 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: So it's inauthentic?

00:47:11.800 --> 00:47:14.891 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: It's inauthentic
and it can convey pity.

00:47:14.891 --> 00:47:15.590 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Hm.

00:47:15.590 --> 00:47:18.870 align:middle line:84%
So my son hated it when people
said I'm sorry because he's,

00:47:18.870 --> 00:47:19.910 align:middle line:90%
like, I'm not a victim.

00:47:19.910 --> 00:47:22.230 align:middle line:84%
Don't throw your
pity party on me.

00:47:22.230 --> 00:47:24.930 align:middle line:90%
So I'm sorry can land like that.

00:47:24.930 --> 00:47:28.260 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's better to
if you knew the person,

00:47:28.260 --> 00:47:31.220 align:middle line:84%
say, gosh, I really--
I really loved Peter.

00:47:31.220 --> 00:47:34.690 align:middle line:84%
And I especially remember this
one time when we went hiking

00:47:34.690 --> 00:47:37.170 align:middle line:84%
or he was so kind when my
son was looking for a job.

00:47:37.170 --> 00:47:38.960 align:middle line:84%
He did da da da-- like,
tell a little story

00:47:38.960 --> 00:47:40.881 align:middle line:84%
about it, that's helpful.
LISA GARR: It is?

00:47:40.881 --> 00:47:41.580 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:47:41.580 --> 00:47:44.650 align:middle line:84%
People love to share
those cherished memories.

00:47:44.650 --> 00:47:46.930 align:middle line:84%
And try not to project
on the other person.

00:47:46.930 --> 00:47:49.690 align:middle line:90%
Let them be wherever they're at.

00:47:49.690 --> 00:47:51.880 align:middle line:90%
Grief is not sadness.

00:47:51.880 --> 00:47:54.130 align:middle line:84%
Grief, as you know
from reading my book,

00:47:54.130 --> 00:47:55.610 align:middle line:84%
it's a whole bunch of
different emotions.

00:47:55.610 --> 00:47:56.400 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yes.

00:47:56.400 --> 00:47:57.799 align:middle line:84%
It's anger.
It's fear.

00:47:57.799 --> 00:47:58.900 align:middle line:90%
It's denial.

00:47:58.900 --> 00:48:01.930 align:middle line:84%
It's a moment of
going I'm alive.

00:48:01.930 --> 00:48:03.494 align:middle line:90%
Wow, what a miracle.

00:48:03.494 --> 00:48:04.330 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Ah, yes.

00:48:04.330 --> 00:48:07.430 align:middle line:84%
Not taking things for
granted, like, huh, life.

00:48:07.430 --> 00:48:08.390 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: That's true.

00:48:08.390 --> 00:48:09.370 align:middle line:90%
Right, right.

00:48:09.370 --> 00:48:13.650 align:middle line:84%
When death brushes us
by, we have a wake-up call

00:48:13.650 --> 00:48:16.150 align:middle line:90%
that we may not have 40 years.

00:48:16.150 --> 00:48:19.020 align:middle line:84%
And so it calls us into,
wow, take a moment.

00:48:19.020 --> 00:48:21.600 align:middle line:90%
Just look at-- enjoy the moment.

00:48:21.600 --> 00:48:22.974 align:middle line:84%
Look at the sunset.
So--

00:48:22.974 --> 00:48:24.140 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And then
you can go back

00:48:24.140 --> 00:48:25.566 align:middle line:84%
to denial and anger
and resentment

00:48:25.566 --> 00:48:26.490 align:middle line:90%
and fear and all that.

00:48:26.490 --> 00:48:27.190 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:48:27.190 --> 00:48:27.950 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And then
you can go back

00:48:27.950 --> 00:48:28.640 align:middle line:90%
into those moments [INAUDIBLE].

00:48:28.640 --> 00:48:30.173 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: But I
think it's like a slinky.

00:48:30.173 --> 00:48:32.950 align:middle line:84%
You go back around-- you come
back around anger or denial.

00:48:32.950 --> 00:48:35.071 align:middle line:84%
But you start on the floor,
and you're working your way up.

00:48:35.071 --> 00:48:35.770 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: OK.

00:48:35.770 --> 00:48:37.780 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so some
good things to say

00:48:37.780 --> 00:48:40.440 align:middle line:84%
are-- you'll remember
this because it'll

00:48:40.440 --> 00:48:42.555 align:middle line:84%
be your truth if this
is what's coming up--

00:48:42.555 --> 00:48:44.180 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what to say.

00:48:44.180 --> 00:48:46.650 align:middle line:90%
Fine, because it's authentic.

00:48:46.650 --> 00:48:49.570 align:middle line:84%
And then the person
will be-- much better

00:48:49.570 --> 00:48:51.520 align:middle line:84%
to have an authentic I
don't know what to say

00:48:51.520 --> 00:48:55.660 align:middle line:90%
than an automatic I'm sorry.

00:48:55.660 --> 00:48:57.920 align:middle line:90%
My heart goes out to you.

00:48:57.920 --> 00:48:58.924 align:middle line:90%
You're not alone.

00:48:58.924 --> 00:49:00.680 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Those are acceptable?
-I'm here.

00:49:00.680 --> 00:49:01.930 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Those are things
you would want to hear?

00:49:01.930 --> 00:49:02.630 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Yes.

00:49:02.630 --> 00:49:03.810 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Hm mm.

00:49:03.810 --> 00:49:06.750 align:middle line:84%
You've got a support
team, and I'm on it.

00:49:06.750 --> 00:49:10.420 align:middle line:84%
But really, it's not so much
about what you say as just

00:49:10.420 --> 00:49:13.610 align:middle line:84%
being willing to
be a space to hear

00:49:13.610 --> 00:49:15.200 align:middle line:90%
whatever's going on for them.

00:49:15.200 --> 00:49:16.340 align:middle line:90%
They may want to talk about it.

00:49:16.340 --> 00:49:17.640 align:middle line:84%
They may not want
to talk about it.

00:49:17.640 --> 00:49:19.600 align:middle line:84%
And that could change
from minute to minute.

00:49:19.600 --> 00:49:20.330 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:49:20.330 --> 00:49:24.126 align:middle line:84%
You had said once is it
OK to say to someone that,

00:49:24.126 --> 00:49:28.850 align:middle line:84%
um-- that there are resources
available, or is that--

00:49:28.850 --> 00:49:30.260 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah,
I think you want to--

00:49:30.260 --> 00:49:33.180 align:middle line:84%
in that initial conversation
with somebody heartbroken,

00:49:33.180 --> 00:49:36.180 align:middle line:84%
your third step would
be around resources.

00:49:36.180 --> 00:49:39.950 align:middle line:84%
But first, you want to
acknowledge the situation;

00:49:39.950 --> 00:49:43.130 align:middle line:84%
then, listen without fixing;
and then, your third step

00:49:43.130 --> 00:49:45.170 align:middle line:84%
is to give hope
and encouragement,

00:49:45.170 --> 00:49:47.780 align:middle line:84%
which could be like there
are resources available.

00:49:47.780 --> 00:49:49.810 align:middle line:84%
There are grief
coaches available.

00:49:49.810 --> 00:49:52.005 align:middle line:84%
You can visit the Grief Coach
Academy-- get some free videos

00:49:52.005 --> 00:49:58.140 align:middle line:84%
or free book, you know,
or other experiences like

00:49:58.140 --> 00:49:59.260 align:middle line:90%
"From Heartbreak to Happiness."

00:49:59.260 --> 00:50:01.390 align:middle line:84%
Initially, I thought that
would be my only gift

00:50:01.390 --> 00:50:02.230 align:middle line:90%
to grieving people.

00:50:02.230 --> 00:50:05.370 align:middle line:84%
And it's helpful to know,
hey, you know, I suffered.

00:50:05.370 --> 00:50:07.240 align:middle line:84%
I was heartbroken,
and I'm happy now.

00:50:07.240 --> 00:50:08.030 align:middle line:90%
I could-- I did it.

00:50:08.030 --> 00:50:08.860 align:middle line:90%
You can, too.

00:50:08.860 --> 00:50:12.380 align:middle line:84%
So encouraging somebody
can show up different ways.

00:50:12.380 --> 00:50:13.670 align:middle line:84%
But you first want
to acknowledge

00:50:13.670 --> 00:50:14.961 align:middle line:90%
and then listen without fixing.

00:50:14.961 --> 00:50:16.860 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Let's talk about
that-- listen without fixing.

00:50:16.860 --> 00:50:18.470 align:middle line:84%
I want to go into
that for a second.

00:50:18.470 --> 00:50:20.230 align:middle line:90%
Is that active listening?

00:50:20.230 --> 00:50:22.607 align:middle line:84%
What is an example of
listen without fixing?

00:50:22.607 --> 00:50:24.040 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: You're
a natural coach here.

00:50:24.040 --> 00:50:25.580 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: I-- I
want to dive in.

00:50:25.580 --> 00:50:26.580 align:middle line:90%
I want to find out.

00:50:26.580 --> 00:50:28.780 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Well, there
are three levels of listening.

00:50:28.780 --> 00:50:30.510 align:middle line:84%
And what we teach at
the Grief Coach Academy

00:50:30.510 --> 00:50:34.350 align:middle line:84%
is to listen with that deep
level three of listening.

00:50:34.350 --> 00:50:37.200 align:middle line:84%
So most people--
normal population--

00:50:37.200 --> 00:50:38.574 align:middle line:90%
they're waiting to talk.

00:50:38.574 --> 00:50:39.540 align:middle line:90%
They're not really listening.

00:50:39.540 --> 00:50:41.044 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Right, right.

00:50:41.044 --> 00:50:42.210 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER:
Level two listening,

00:50:42.210 --> 00:50:46.360 align:middle line:84%
you hear what the person
is literally saying.

00:50:46.360 --> 00:50:48.860 align:middle line:84%
But level three of listening,
you hear what they're saying.

00:50:48.860 --> 00:50:51.547 align:middle line:84%
And you hear also
the hidden messages--

00:50:51.547 --> 00:50:52.280 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Underneath.

00:50:52.280 --> 00:50:55.060 align:middle line:84%
---underneath, and
you meet them where

00:50:55.060 --> 00:50:56.970 align:middle line:90%
their emotional energy is.

00:50:56.970 --> 00:50:59.200 align:middle line:84%
So somebody might
say the same thing,

00:50:59.200 --> 00:51:02.840 align:middle line:84%
and I would respond
quite differently

00:51:02.840 --> 00:51:05.340 align:middle line:84%
depending on what's not
being said-- you know,

00:51:05.340 --> 00:51:06.570 align:middle line:90%
the energy around it.

00:51:06.570 --> 00:51:09.320 align:middle line:84%
So somebody might
say, oh, I just found

00:51:09.320 --> 00:51:11.830 align:middle line:90%
out my mom has got cancer.

00:51:11.830 --> 00:51:15.030 align:middle line:84%
It's like, you know, level
two listening-- well,

00:51:15.030 --> 00:51:18.260 align:middle line:84%
level one listening is, oh,
well, my friend had cancer,

00:51:18.260 --> 00:51:19.740 align:middle line:84%
and she died last week.
Not good.

00:51:19.740 --> 00:51:20.540 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Right, right.

00:51:20.540 --> 00:51:23.010 align:middle line:84%
Level two listening is, oh,
they have this new cancer

00:51:23.010 --> 00:51:24.030 align:middle line:90%
resource available.

00:51:24.030 --> 00:51:25.200 align:middle line:90%
That's still not too great.

00:51:25.200 --> 00:51:26.710 align:middle line:84%
But level three
listening might be

00:51:26.710 --> 00:51:29.310 align:middle line:84%
to hear that she
wants some support,

00:51:29.310 --> 00:51:33.240 align:middle line:84%
and say, oh, wow, you
know, tell me about it.

00:51:33.240 --> 00:51:37.420 align:middle line:84%
Or would you like to come over
so I can have dinner with you?

00:51:37.420 --> 00:51:39.080 align:middle line:84%
Or what was your
relationship like--

00:51:39.080 --> 00:51:42.620 align:middle line:84%
good, fair, poor, mixed-- give
her an opportunity to share.

00:51:42.620 --> 00:51:45.960 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: So go and just
allow the space and be quiet.

00:51:45.960 --> 00:51:49.210 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah, one of
the keys to being a great coach

00:51:49.210 --> 00:51:53.750 align:middle line:84%
is to have befriended every
part of your own life.

00:51:53.750 --> 00:51:56.820 align:middle line:84%
The reason why most people
aren't good listeners is

00:51:56.820 --> 00:51:59.890 align:middle line:84%
because, if I said to you,
I just found out my mom's

00:51:59.890 --> 00:52:02.310 align:middle line:84%
got cancer, all the
buttons within you,

00:52:02.310 --> 00:52:04.400 align:middle line:84%
you know-- what if
my mom gets cancer?

00:52:04.400 --> 00:52:06.000 align:middle line:90%
What if I get cancer?

00:52:06.000 --> 00:52:07.650 align:middle line:84%
What if-- you know,
all that comes up.

00:52:07.650 --> 00:52:11.760 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't leave you
available to be a really great

00:52:11.760 --> 00:52:14.266 align:middle line:84%
coach to-- I'm not saying
you personally, but you know,

00:52:14.266 --> 00:52:15.610 align:middle line:84%
as an example.
LISA GARR: Right, yeah.

00:52:15.610 --> 00:52:17.820 align:middle line:84%
And so part of
being a great coach

00:52:17.820 --> 00:52:23.190 align:middle line:84%
is to really befriend and
transcend all of your buttons

00:52:23.190 --> 00:52:24.510 align:middle line:90%
so that you can be there.

00:52:24.510 --> 00:52:26.240 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: I think
everyone can use

00:52:26.240 --> 00:52:27.520 align:middle line:90%
that advice, Aurora, really.

00:52:27.520 --> 00:52:31.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's-- listening is
such an important part of being

00:52:31.340 --> 00:52:34.530 align:middle line:84%
a person and to have the first
word out of your mouth always

00:52:34.530 --> 00:52:36.810 align:middle line:90%
be "I" is so disconnecting.

00:52:36.810 --> 00:52:38.440 align:middle line:90%
I'm very sensitive to that.

00:52:38.440 --> 00:52:41.290 align:middle line:84%
And yes, to have-- to even when
you're talking with a friend

00:52:41.290 --> 00:52:44.670 align:middle line:84%
about a bad day or if it's
a situation that happened,

00:52:44.670 --> 00:52:47.755 align:middle line:84%
oh, I had a situation like
that doesn't serve anyone.

00:52:47.755 --> 00:52:49.520 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: No.
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:49.520 --> 00:52:51.150 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: No, it doesn't.

00:52:51.150 --> 00:52:54.310 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Just-- just a little
moment of awareness that I-- I

00:52:54.310 --> 00:52:55.291 align:middle line:90%
appreciate you saying that.

00:52:55.291 --> 00:52:56.490 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah,
and that's what

00:52:56.490 --> 00:52:58.340 align:middle line:90%
I love about the Peace Method.

00:52:58.340 --> 00:53:02.220 align:middle line:84%
It invites you to listen
to yourself, you know,

00:53:02.220 --> 00:53:03.870 align:middle line:84%
because you can
do it by yourself

00:53:03.870 --> 00:53:05.230 align:middle line:90%
as a journaling process.

00:53:05.230 --> 00:53:06.710 align:middle line:90%
And there's great wisdom there.

00:53:06.710 --> 00:53:08.160 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Self-censoring--
a little bit,

00:53:08.160 --> 00:53:09.310 align:middle line:90%
yeah, a little bit, yes.

00:53:09.310 --> 00:53:14.170 align:middle line:84%
So have you seen people really
transform grief in 30 minutes--

00:53:14.170 --> 00:53:16.500 align:middle line:90%
one chunk at a time?

00:53:16.500 --> 00:53:19.330 align:middle line:84%
As it is-- I mean, what have
you seen in your experience?

00:53:19.330 --> 00:53:21.700 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: I like to under
promise and over deliver.

00:53:21.700 --> 00:53:23.720 align:middle line:84%
But the honest
answer to that is I

00:53:23.720 --> 00:53:27.100 align:middle line:84%
have seen people have one
30-minute session with me

00:53:27.100 --> 00:53:29.470 align:middle line:90%
and have a life-changing shift.

00:53:29.470 --> 00:53:30.740 align:middle line:90%
I'm not guaranteeing that.

00:53:30.740 --> 00:53:32.450 align:middle line:84%
It's not every time, but--
LISA GARR: Right.

00:53:32.450 --> 00:53:36.170 align:middle line:84%
It-- it-- it has happened
that people have had something

00:53:36.170 --> 00:53:38.860 align:middle line:84%
weighing on their heart
for 4 and 1/2 years--

00:53:38.860 --> 00:53:40.561 align:middle line:84%
really grieving.
One session--

00:53:40.561 --> 00:53:41.260 align:middle line:90%
[SNAPS]

00:53:41.260 --> 00:53:44.050 align:middle line:84%
---less than half
an hour, completely

00:53:44.050 --> 00:53:45.750 align:middle line:90%
seeing it another way.

00:53:45.750 --> 00:53:47.400 align:middle line:84%
And that woman, you
know, said her eyes

00:53:47.400 --> 00:53:48.630 align:middle line:90%
were a different color.

00:53:48.630 --> 00:53:50.330 align:middle line:84%
She had joy in her
heart that she hadn't

00:53:50.330 --> 00:53:52.210 align:middle line:90%
felt for 4 and 1/2 years.

00:53:52.210 --> 00:53:54.230 align:middle line:84%
Three months later, I
checked in with her.

00:53:54.230 --> 00:53:57.100 align:middle line:84%
She was able to make more
money, be more joyful,

00:53:57.100 --> 00:53:59.920 align:middle line:84%
be more present for her
kids, started dating-- like,

00:53:59.920 --> 00:54:02.440 align:middle line:84%
her whole life shifted
from one 30-minute session.

00:54:02.440 --> 00:54:03.760 align:middle line:90%
I don't guarantee that.

00:54:03.760 --> 00:54:04.460 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Right.

00:54:04.460 --> 00:54:05.777 align:middle line:90%
But it-- even if--

00:54:05.777 --> 00:54:06.910 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Her
life started again.

00:54:06.910 --> 00:54:09.930 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Her life--
yeah, her life started again.

00:54:09.930 --> 00:54:12.010 align:middle line:84%
It's like a booster
cable on a car.

00:54:12.010 --> 00:54:13.460 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And I-- I've
always wondered-- I

00:54:13.460 --> 00:54:14.840 align:middle line:90%
always ask you about your son.

00:54:14.840 --> 00:54:17.260 align:middle line:84%
In his process of
grieving-- and I

00:54:17.260 --> 00:54:22.010 align:middle line:84%
know you have a lot of great
advice for parents of children

00:54:22.010 --> 00:54:26.320 align:middle line:84%
who are dealing with grief,
as well-- how is your son now?

00:54:26.320 --> 00:54:28.870 align:middle line:84%
And how has he coped
with everything, and--

00:54:28.870 --> 00:54:29.870 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: He's so great.

00:54:29.870 --> 00:54:32.570 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my biggest worry
was was my son going

00:54:32.570 --> 00:54:34.590 align:middle line:84%
to be permanently
damaged from his dad

00:54:34.590 --> 00:54:35.770 align:middle line:90%
dying when he was only four?

00:54:35.770 --> 00:54:38.980 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that so
weighed on my heart.

00:54:38.980 --> 00:54:40.960 align:middle line:84%
And I did everything I
could to try to help him.

00:54:40.960 --> 00:54:43.030 align:middle line:84%
But the quick answer
on that is the best

00:54:43.030 --> 00:54:44.505 align:middle line:84%
thing parents can do
to help their kids

00:54:44.505 --> 00:54:45.690 align:middle line:90%
is get support yourself.

00:54:45.690 --> 00:54:48.460 align:middle line:84%
Because once mommy was
fine, my son, you know,

00:54:48.460 --> 00:54:49.660 align:middle line:90%
worked through his grief.

00:54:49.660 --> 00:54:49.880 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: That makes
sense because you're

00:54:49.880 --> 00:54:51.170 align:middle line:90%
always going to be a model.

00:54:51.170 --> 00:54:52.070 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah.

00:54:52.070 --> 00:54:53.300 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And how
you relate to it

00:54:53.300 --> 00:54:54.780 align:middle line:84%
is how they're going
to relate to it.

00:54:54.780 --> 00:54:55.410 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: Yeah, so--
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:54:55.410 --> 00:54:58.380 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: It took-- he
grieved when the dog died

00:54:58.380 --> 00:54:59.480 align:middle line:90%
four years after Daddy died.

00:54:59.480 --> 00:55:00.410 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Ah, OK.

00:55:00.410 --> 00:55:04.920 align:middle line:84%
And then, whoa, the tears-- but
it wasn't just about the dog.

00:55:04.920 --> 00:55:05.880 align:middle line:90%
It was about his father.

00:55:05.880 --> 00:55:07.550 align:middle line:90%
But by then, I was grounded.

00:55:07.550 --> 00:55:09.880 align:middle line:84%
He knew I could hold
a space for him.

00:55:09.880 --> 00:55:12.760 align:middle line:84%
Kids are so sensitive to
how's mommy and daddy doing.

00:55:12.760 --> 00:55:14.219 align:middle line:84%
So--
LISA GARR: Yeah.

00:55:14.219 --> 00:55:15.880 align:middle line:84%
Quick answer--
focus on yourself.

00:55:15.880 --> 00:55:18.290 align:middle line:84%
That is the biggest
gift for your child.

00:55:18.290 --> 00:55:21.130 align:middle line:84%
But my son now is
designing video games.

00:55:21.130 --> 00:55:22.330 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Oh, so he's thriving.

00:55:22.330 --> 00:55:23.045 align:middle line:90%
He's thriving.

00:55:23.045 --> 00:55:25.310 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: And you help
so many people thrive.

00:55:25.310 --> 00:55:27.330 align:middle line:90%
And I so appreciate what you do.

00:55:27.330 --> 00:55:30.580 align:middle line:84%
And to assist you in any
way to get your message out,

00:55:30.580 --> 00:55:32.767 align:middle line:84%
I am so grateful to be able
to have the opportunity to do.

00:55:32.767 --> 00:55:33.600 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Thank you.

00:55:33.600 --> 00:55:35.984 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much, Aurora.

00:55:35.984 --> 00:55:37.750 align:middle line:84%
AURORA WINTER: It's an honor
and privilege to be part

00:55:37.750 --> 00:55:39.444 align:middle line:84%
of whatever you're doing, Lisa.
You're awesome.

00:55:39.444 --> 00:55:41.110 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Well, I got to
say that you are a gift.

00:55:41.110 --> 00:55:41.560 align:middle line:90%
AURORA WINTER: Thank you.

00:55:41.560 --> 00:55:43.320 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much--
and to so many people

00:55:43.320 --> 00:55:45.250 align:middle line:84%
who heard your
messages and they went

00:55:45.250 --> 00:55:46.910 align:middle line:90%
right through to their hearts.

00:55:46.910 --> 00:55:48.960 align:middle line:84%
And I can feel
that that happened.

